title: beef loaf with ketchup
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except ketchup.
Pour the ketchup in bottom of well-greased ring pan.
Pack in mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn out of mold, ketchup side up.
Fill with hot potato salad.
If loaf is to be served cold, potato salad may be chilled.

title: orange delight cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and peach pie filling with fork 1 minute.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Bake in ungreased pan, 9 x 13-inch, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn, salt, sugar, flour and melted margarine; add beaten eggs and milk.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 350°
for 35 minutes or until firm.

title: gather-round pound cake
directions: Melt together in pan butterscotch chips, coffee and water. Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in butterscotch mixture.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat at medium speed.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool before removing.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Cook pineapple and sugar together until sugar is dissolved. Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix pineapple and jello together. Chill until thick.
Toss cheese, pecans and whipped cream into jello mixture.
Chill thoroughly.

title: snow balls
directions: Mix well and drop teaspoons into hot grease. Roll in sugar.

title: old-fashioned soda bread
directions: In a bowl, combine wheat flour and all-purpose flour.
Add baking powder, baking soda, sugar and salt.
Add yogurt or buttermilk.
Mix and knead until a soft dough forms.
It should still feel wet.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and set aside.
Saute celery and onion in margarine; add soup and mushrooms.
Melt cheese.
Mix everything together.

title: lime pineapple salad
directions: Use juice from pineapple and water to make 4 cups liquid; dissolve jello and gelatin with this liquid, 2 cups hot liquid and 2 cups cold liquid.
Stir in cream cheese to melt.
When thick, add pineapple and nuts.
Put in refrigerator to congeal.

title: swedish fish casserole
directions: Drain salmon.
Alternate layers of potatoes, salmon and onion in a greased large casserole.
Sprinkle each potato layer with flour, salt and pepper.
End with salmon layer.
Beat egg with milk.
Pour over top, adding enough milk to cover.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove cover and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: orange liqueur
directions: Pare very thinly the brightly colored rind from the oranges (no white).
Blot peel on paper towel to remove any excess oil.
Put peel in a four cup, screw-type jar.
Add two cups vodka.
Close jar.
Store in a cool, dark place for 2 days or until vodka has absorbed the flavor and color of the peel.
Remove peel; add sugar and shake vigorously until sugar dissolves.
Add remaining cup of vodka and stir until liquid becomes clear.
Close jar and cool in a cool, dark place.

title: crisp date delight
directions: Melt butter or margarine; add sugar and stir well over medium heat.
While stirring add dates, nuts and eggs; continue to stir and heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in crisp rice, cool and shape into balls (1 1/2-inch).
Roll in coconut.
Crisp rice is about the same as Rice Krispies.

title: party pieces
directions: Brown ground chuck and hot sausage in skillet until done. Drain.
Slice or cube Velveeta cheese and add to ground chuck and hot sausage. Simmer until cheese is melted.
Serve on small squares of party rye bread or whatever you prefer.

title: spice tea mix
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.
To serve, add 1 to 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to 1 cup of hot water.

title: lettuce herb salad
directions: Layer in order given. Toss and chill. When ready to use, toss again.

title: coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage and set aside.
Chop onion small; add to cabbage.
Combine remaining ingredients in pan and cook over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Cook sauce until thick.
Mix with cabbage and onion.
Serve warm.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; put into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: keftethes 2
directions: Mix ingredients together,
except
tomato
sauce.
Form into desired size of
meatball.	Roll
the meatballs in flour; place in shallow pan and place
in
oven.
Bake
in	400° oven until brown. When done, place
meatballs in deep pot and pour in tomato sauce and water
mixture,
adding salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon vinegar. Simmer for
hour.
(The
tomato
sauce should cover the meatballs.)

title: pimento cheese
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl. Add first 5 ingredients.
Process until smooth. Add pimento.
Pulse 4 or 5 times.
This has only 27 calories and 2 g. fat.

title: ham noodle skillet
directions: Drain canned mushrooms, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Set aside. Saute ham, green pepper and onion in margarine in a large skillet.
Stir in black pepper, paprika and Worcestershire sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Brown butter slightly; add to sugar and Karo.
Mix well.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: turkey parmesan
directions: On waxed paper, mix flour, salt and pepper.
On another sheet, mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.

title: icebox cake
directions: Melt chocolate, sugar and water together.
Cool slightly. Cream butter or half and half with confectioners sugar.
Add to mixture and stir in 1 egg.
Spread between graham crackers, one on top of the other, about 6 high.
Let set, then slice diagonally.

title: persimmon pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in persimmon pulp, milk, egg and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool.
You might like to use apple pie spices instead of the 2 listed, at least 1 teaspoon.

title: very best fat-free fudge brownies
directions: Melt chocolate in small saucepan and cook over low heat.
Stir until melted.
Add sugar, egg substitute, prune butter and vanilla to chocolate.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and, if desired, salt and nuts.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, pepper and onion.
Mix vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise and fold into cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: salsa
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour jar of spaghetti sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese over sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
The last ten minutes of baking time, sprinkle grated Mozzarella cheese on top and place pan back into the oven until the cheese melts. (Let cool slightly before serving.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato and onions. Spoon mixture into 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until slightly browned. Serve with crackers or pita bread triangles.

title: fancy man's (alias texas walker) shrimp and crab dip
directions: Drain shrimp and 3/4 can crab meat and mix together with cream cheese.
Top with cocktail sauce (or ketchup and horseradish mixture).

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken, onion and garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes, sauce, seasonings and peppers.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: old-fashioned squash pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, flour and spices together in a large bowl.
Beat eggs and add to the sugar mixture.
Stir in squash and cream.
Pour into the shell and bake 50 minutes, or until the center is set.
Cool before serving with whipped cream. Serves 8 to 10.

title: no bake date cookies
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in heavy saucepan or skillet on top of stove; stir until it starts to boil and then cook 6 minutes until thickened.
Remove from heat and add the nuts and Krispies. Form into balls (small) and roll in flaked coconut.
Makes about 50.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray muffin pans with nonstick vegetable coating.
Combine dry ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
In another bowl, combine other ingredients, except raisins and mix well.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients and stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not overmix.
Stir in raisins and fill prepared muffin pans 3/4 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Mix the remaining ingredients for topping.
Put topping on. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soups, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder in small saucepan.
Heat
until
just warm.
In 3 quart baking dish, layer
broccoli, chicken, soup mixture, water chestnuts, bread crumbs, cheese
and
almonds.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Wash, core, peel and thinly slice apples.
Brush slices with lemon juice.
Toss apple slices with a mixture of the sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Fill pastry shell with apple mixture and dot with butter.
Cover apples with second pastry.
Prick top crust with fork.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 40 minutes longer.

title: cinnamon popcorn
directions: Put popcorn in large bowl.
In a saucepan, combine oleo, syrup and candies.
Bring to a boil over medium heat stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour over popcorn and mix.
Turn into baking pan.
When cold, break in pieces.
Store in plastic bags.
Rice Krispies can be used.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix well.
Add sifted flour and baking powder, alternating with milk to first mixture.
Then add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and other vegetables. Mix together. Combine other ingredients. Mix thoroughly.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Melt yeast in warm water.
Combine all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
Use as much as needed at time until all used up.

title: excellent vegetable dip
directions: Stir together sugar, vinegar and butter.
Add egg yolks.
Stir slowly and constantly over medium-low heat until just below the boiling point. Mixture will be blended and thickened.
Cool completely. Combine and stir in all other ingredients. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk; set aside.
Mix cake mix and rest of milk, butter and pecans.
Put 1/2 of cake mix in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over cake, then drizzle caramel mixture on top.
Pour remaining cake mix on top of caramels.
Bake 18 minutes more at 350°.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: In saucepan, cook green pepper with garlic in oil until tender.
Blend in soup and pineapple juice. Add chicken, pineapple and soy sauce. Heat and serve over rice. Top with almonds. Serves 6.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Take oil, garlic, onion and pepper and saute to get aroma. Place cleaned chicken pieces in pot.
Brown.
Add 1 can crushed tomatoes and sprinkle oregano.
Add 2 to 3 bay leaves.
Let cook for 10 minutes.
Then add potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are soft enough.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put a thin layer of stuffing mix in a buttered casserole.
Mix all other ingredients and pour onto stuffing mix layer.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Cook rice according to instructions and add sausages (cut up or whole), about halfway through.
Stir occasionally until done.

title: crispix peanut butter snack
directions: In large saucepan, bring corn syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until well blended.
Gently add Crispix; stir until well coated.
Spread cereal mixture onto well-greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Melt chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Drizzle over top of cereal mixture.
Chill.
Break cereal mixture into bite-size pieces.

title: noodle and hamburg casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water; drain.
Fry all remaining ingredients.
Alternate layer of noodles, then a layer of meat, then a layer of noodles.
Pour tomato soup on top of noodles. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt virginia's 6-week bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins.
Add soda; let cool.
Sift flour into extra large mixing bowl.
Save 1/2 cup flour for nuts. Add salt, cereals and floured nuts.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Fold in raisin mixture.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Mix until moistened.
Cover.
Store in refrigerator.
When needed, fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake at 375°.
Refrigerate unused portion.

title: de-von casserole
directions: Fry bacon and chip up.
Set aside.
Boil egg noodles in margarine until tender; drain.
Mix eggs and Parmesan cheese by hand.
Mix in whipping cream until smooth.
Pour over egg mixture and noodles in casserole dish.
Sprinkle bacon and Cheddar cheese on top and bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: roast pork with apricot glaze
directions: Score roast (cut across it diagonally).
Rub with salt and pepper and stick with whole cloves.
Place on rack in open roasting pan with fat side up.
Roast at 350° for 35 minutes per pound.
Simmer apricots in water until tender.
Pour off juice and save 1 cup of liquid.
Set apricots aside.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and apricot juice.
During last 30 minutes of baking time, spoon over meat, basting often until pork has golden glaze.

title: sex in a pan
directions: Mix together chopped pecans, 1/2 cup butter, 1 cup flour and 3 tablespoons sugar and put in a 9 x 16-inch greased pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix Philadelphia cream cheese, icing or confectioners sugar and 1/2 tub Cool Whip.
Mix together and spread on cooled base.

title: zesty coleslaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, salad dressing, mustard and paprika in a small bowl; add to cabbage mixture and toss until well mixed.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Yields 12 (1/2 cup) servings (approximately 28 calories and 1.75 g fat).

title: mexican quiche
directions: Crumble ground beef into 1-quart casserole. Cover with glass lid.
Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes on high until browned.
Drain well.
Sprinkle over bottom of baked crust.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Combine flour, cocoa, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture; mix. Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: easy appetizer
directions: Trim off crust of bread.
Flatten slices with rolling pin. Spread each slice with 1 teaspoon of soup.
Cut in half, roll up (jelly roll like).
Wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around each roll. Place on broiler sheet with drip pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes about 50 appetizers.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ground beef until tender; drain.
Saute onions and garlic until tender.
Combine all ingredients; cook for 1 hour very slow.
Serve over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: honey mustard salad dressing
directions: Mix oil and vinegar; add honey and mustard.
Shake well and keep refrigerated.
Great for salads or over pasta or rice.
May be used as a marinade.
For a creamy style, add 1/4 cup nonfat plain yogurt.

title: bird in a nest
directions: I wake Dad up with a hug and a kiss and ask can you fix me some French toast?

title: striped delight
directions: Mix together the graham crackers and butter and press into a 9 x 13 pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, sugar, milk and 1/2 of the Kool Whip.
Set aside.
Pour both vanilla and chocolate pudding into a bowl and add milk.
Mix until thick.
Place the cream cheese mixture over the graham cracker crust.
Add the pudding mixture. Just before serving, add the remaining Kool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Put all ingredients into Sunbeam blender.
Cover and process at chop until smooth.
Chill.

title: peaches and cream cheese cake
directions: Combine flour, pudding, egg and milk.
Beat for two minutes and place in 9 to 10-inch pie pan.
Place peaches over batter.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Slice each apple into about 8 to 10 slices.
Cream the cheese with the sugars.
Stir in vanilla and nuts; serve with apples. Better with skins left on apples!

title: coffee mocha punch
directions: Mix coffee, half of ice cream, almond, dash of salt and sugar. Fold in rest of ice cream and whipped cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll in pecans and refrigerate.
Eat with crackers.

title: karen's kugel
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Boil noodles for 5 minutes with a little bit of oil; drain and run cold water over noodles.
Blend all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Place blended mixture in a lasagna dish; sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 5 minutes, then at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serves 18 hungry people or 24 less hungry people.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Mix the mashed potatoes, sugar, cornstarch and peanut butter together.
With your hands, work the mixture into small egg sized balls.

title: glenda mcelhanon's green bean casserole
directions: Put green beans with juice in pan.
Add 1/2 chopped onion and boil until onion is soft.
Drain well.
Add butter, mushroom soup and cheese.
Stir well and put in a casserole dish.
Place onion rings on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl on low speed, combine cake mix, 1 egg, butter and 2 teaspoons pie spice.
Mix until crumbly. Press in 15 x 10-inch pan.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk, then eggs and mashed cooked sweet potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well, pour over crust and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool, chill and cut in bars.

title: never fail icing
directions: Place egg white, sugar and water in top of double boiler. Place in boiling water; keep boiling.
Beat constantly with eggbeater 7 minutes.
Add flavoring.
This is ready to use at once. If desired, add 1 cup of marshmallows cut up to frosting before spreading.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole.
Mix 1 cup flour with 1 cup milk, 1 stick butter and baking powder.
Beat with mixer until smooth; pour over chicken and bake until done at 400°.

title: paul bunyan burgers
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add ground beef and seasonings.
Mix lightly to blend.
Pat beef in circle or square on wax paper. Cover beef with catsup, mustard, relish, onion, cheese, etc. leaving margarine for sealing.
Fold over and seal.
Broil slowly.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugars and shortening; add egg and beat.
Mix dry ingredients together and add alternately with sour milk.
Add rhubarb.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage and onion.
Cook noodles; drain.
Add noodles, soup, cheese, milk and oregano to sausage and onion.
Add extra cheese on top.
Brown in a casserole dish for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: patrick e.'s pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let set at least 6 hours or overnight.

title: tuna casserole(for 4 people)
directions: In kettle, cook egg noodles until tender.
In a saucepan, cook tuna, soups, butter, celery salt, pepper and the milk until hot. Mix with drained egg noodles.
Put into casserole dish.
Crush potato chips or crackers on top.
Bake until bubbly, about 30 minutes, at 350°.

title: quick and easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish. Add fruit with juice and heat to boiling. Mix sugar, flour, egg and pour this mixture over hot fruit. Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: noodles and broccoli
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Steam broccoli; drain.
Mix together the spaghetti, broccoli, soup and milk.
Heat until hot, but do not overcook.
Sprinkle cheese on top before serving.

title: mint-flavored greek meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape mixture into 1 inch balls.
(For easy shaping, dip hands into cold water from time to time.)
Place meatballs in ungreased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) or oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven until light brown, about 25 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: ham delights
directions: Blend margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion.
Spread mixture on top of ham and cheese on rolls.
Place tops of rolls back on bottoms; wrap in foil.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until completely hot throughout.
May freeze.

title: homemade lemonade
directions: Mix lemon juice, water and sugar together.
Pour in cups and add ice cubes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook milk, flour, cocoa, sugar, salt and egg yolks until thick.
Add vanilla and butter; set aside to cool, while beating egg whites.
Cover pie with meringue.
Bake at 325° until brown, about 25 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven.
Roll chicken in butter.
Add onions.
Place in oven to brown top of chicken.
Remove from oven, turn chicken and return to oven to brown.
Add mushroom soup and water.
Return to oven and simmer at 375° to 400°.
Prepare rice according to package directions; pour gravy from chicken over rice.

title: flat bread
directions: Cream the lard and sugar. Add soda with buttermilk and oatmeal.
Mix in the 3 cups buttermilk alternately with the flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Roll with some corn meal and flour as needed.
Bake on a lefse grill at about 425° and then dry in a 250° to 275° oven.

title: special corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix with oats, eggs, vegetable oil, milk, raisins, nuts and brown sugar. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 12 minutes; transfer to wire rack to cool.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: curry tuna or chicken rice salad
directions: Combine ingredients through rice.
Place rice mixture in serving bowl and arrange chicken or tuna over rice.

title: gramma ginny's jage
directions: In a large metal pot with cover, saute sliced linguica and chopped onions in bacon fat until onions are clear; add seasonings. Stir in rice.
Cover with water, just enough to cover all the rice. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Pour in peas (drained) and stick of butter.
Stir with a silver fork (not a spoon).
Serve hot.
Great with barbecue.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt butter; add cocoa and stir until dissolved.
Add hot water and stir again with wire whip.
Blend in sugar, flour, salt, vanilla extract and evaporated milk.
Stir until butter is smooth. Mix in pecans and pour into pie crust.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet for 50 minutes or until custard sets.
Garnish with nondairy whipped topping.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: dill pickles for 11 quarts
directions: Bring the ingredients to a boil and pour over pickles with a ball of dill in the bottom of jar and 1 clove garlic.
Fill jars with pickles and solution, then cold pack.
Just let them come to a good boil and take off.
These pickles are real crisp and they are delicious.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in oven for 30 minutes at 325° or microwave.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into crock-pot.
Heat thoroughly. Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: chocolate cheesecake pie
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature and whip.
Melt chocolate; add to cream cheese.
Spoon in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust; chill for 3 to 4 hours, then serve.

title: chicken dumpling pie
directions: Combine chicken, soup, broth, Veg-All and poultry seasoning. Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan. Combine biscuit mix, sour cream and milk in a bowl; mix well and pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until pie is golden brown.

title: blue crab appetizer
directions: Mix ingredients together and spoon into large scallop baking shells.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: kentucky pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, oil, applesauce, baking powder, cinnamon, hot water, and egg yolks; beat at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in chopped pecans. Beat egg whites until stiff then fold into the batter.
Pour the mixture into an ungreased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes. Invert the pan and cool the cake completely before removing from the pan.
Sprinkle the top of the cake with powdered sugar.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Drain.
Add other ingredients.
Heat to boiling, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over toasted buns.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy, add sugar and peanut butter; beat.
Add milk and blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie shell. Sprinkle peanuts on top.
Refrigerate or you can freeze.

title: hot ham salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in oiled casserole and top with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cream the Cheez Whiz, soup and butter together. Add rest of ingredients and bake in a greased casserole at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix melted butter, flour and chopped pecans; press into the bottom of a rectangle Pyrex dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Next mix together softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour this on cooled crust.

title: hawaiian fruit cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs. Add salt and baking powder. Mix in crushed pineapple. Add coconut, walnuts or pecans, vanilla and rum.

title: beverly's dill bread
directions: Warm cheese and butter slightly.
Add dill, onion, sugar, soda, salt and eggs.
Beat until blended.
Combine water and yeast; stir until blended.
Stir into cheese mixture.
Add flour. Knead.
Let rise.
Shape into 2 (8 x 4-inch) loaves.
Rise to top of pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon melted butter on bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put layer of cherry filling; sprinkle cake mix over, then layer of pineapple, then coconut.
Repeat until all is used. Melt the butter or margarine; pour on top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Pour boiling water over zucchini in large bowl.
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2. Heat oven to 350°.
Beat zucchini mixture and remaining ingredients on medium speed, scraping bowl constantly until blended, about 1 minute.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 2 minutes more.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan, if desired.
Cool completely.

title: puppy chow (snack)
directions: Melt
first
3 ingredients and stir until well blended, then put
in large bowl and stir in cereal until well coated. Put
in a
large
plastic
bag and pour in powdered sugar and shake vigorously until coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: apple, tomato and raisin chutney
directions: Quarter the tomatoes and puree them in a blender or food processor, or mash well with a fork.
Simmer them, along with the onions, in a heavy pot.
Stir occasionally, adding a bit of water if the tomatoes have not produced enough liquid to prevent the mixture from sticking.
After 45 minutes, add all the remaining ingredients except apples and cook until you have
a thick paste suitable for spooning.
When cooking curry, the time can vary greatly.
Add the apples and cook another half hour.
Spoon into clean jars; cap and refrigerate when cool.
The chutney will keep 4 to 6 weeks.

title: food for the gods
directions: Beat yolks until lemon colored.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold egg whites into the egg yolks.
Add vanilla. Fold in all other ingredients.
Bake in 8 x 12-inch baking dish until light brown at 350° for 35 minutes.
When cool, crumble and serve with whipped cream.

title: empanadas
directions: Thaw pastry dough.
Cut with 2 1/2 to 3-inch round cookie cutter until all dough is used.
Fry ground beef and drain grease. Add seasoning as directed on package.
Spoon 1 teaspoon of mixture onto each circle of dough.
Mix cheeses and put about 1 teaspoonful on meat mixture.
Fold circle in half and seal edges, making a pocket of meat and cheese.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in preheated oven at 350° until light brown.

title: microwave baked beans and beef
directions: Lightly brown meat and onion, stirring to break up meat.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into microwave-safe dish and microwave for 15 minutes on High.

title: hearty cheese soup
directions: Place margarine and onion in microproof dish and cook on 90% power (saute) for 3 minutes
or until onions are transparent. Combine salt, pepper and flour with milk. Heat onions, milk mixture and broth in large pot on stove on medium-high heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted. If needed, thicken soup with cornstarch mixed with extra chicken broth.
(This soup is also good with cooked cauliflower or carrots added.)

title: "baked" beans
directions: Drain sauce off of pork and beans and take out fat pieces. Cut Sizzlean into 1-inch pieces.
Cook Sizzlean in a 2-quart saucepan until firm, but not crisp.
Add beans and brown sugar to taste.
Simmer over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch snack cake
directions: In large saucepan combine pudding mix and milk.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in dry cake mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with butterscotch chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Use "fresh from the patch" beets about 1 1/2-inches in diameter. Cut off tops, leaving about 1-inch on the beets. Scrub and put in large pot to boil.

title: sad or flop cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beer batter
directions: Beat egg white, stiff; add beaten yolks and remaining ingredients.
Excellent for deep fried clams, oysters or shrimp.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Mix in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread over creamed mixture.
Top with remaining topping (Cool Whip). Sprinkle shaved chocolate (or mini chocolate chips) and chopped nuts on top.
Refrigerate.

title: pork chops and pork and beans
directions: Brown pork chops fast.
In bowl, put beans, sugar, ketchup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Cut onions in slices and pull apart.
Drain grease off of pork chops.
Put back in pan on low heat.
Pour other ingredients over pork chops.
Let simmer 45 minutes.
Then enjoy your tender pork chops and beans.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together well. Boil franks and roll in flour, then dip in batter and deep fry until golden.

title: marinated vegies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vegetables.
Add mixture to vegetables.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: cole slaw
directions: Bring to a rolling boil.
While hot, pour over slaw mixture. Refrigerate 24 hours before
serving.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on box.
Remove from heat.
Add the chocolate cake mix; beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle on top the chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: boiled cookies (t.v. snacks)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil over medium heat. Boil for 1 minute. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Drop on foil or wax paper. Cools quickly.

title: graham pecan cookies
directions: Grease the bottom of a cookie sheet with sides.
Place graham crackers over entire surface.
Put brown sugar and margarine in a saucepan.
Boil about 2 minutes.
Add pecans and bring to a boil again.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350 ° for 10 minutes; then cut while still warm.

title: too easy fruit salad
directions: Read entire recipe before beginning:

title: swiss chard with onions
directions: Wash and slice crosswise into 1-inch lengths the young stalks of Swiss chard using stem and leaf.
Saute thinly sliced green onions in oil until golden in color.
If using bacon, add it to the onions and saute until it is lightly browned.
Add chard and saute briefly, just until it is tender but has not lost its green color.
Salt to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 1 cup salad dressing or enough to mix ingredients together.
Chill.
Delicious as a sandwich spread or served on lettuce.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
No need to chill.
Roll out and cut with a glass or cookie cutter.
Put on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Boil hamburger meat, salt, potato and 1 cup of onions, then mash.
Soft fry tortillas and roll with meat mixture, cheese and onion.
Mix enchilada sauce, mushroom soup and 1 can of water. Pour over rolled stuffed tortillas.
Top with leftover cheese and onions.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off fat.
Add next 6 ingredients. Simmer uncovered 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles. Meanwhile, combine cottage cheese, Ricotta cheese, eggs, seasonings and Parmesan cheese.
Place half of the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread half of the cheese mixture over noodles. Add half of the Mozzarella cheese and top with half of the sauce. Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with triangles of Mozzarella cheese.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: creamy thousand island dressing
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and make a paste.
Add milk and stir until thickened.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted. Add salt and pepper.
Slice potatoes and place a layer of them in a 3 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/3 of the onions over the potatoes.
Pour 1/3 of sauce over potatoes and onions.
Repeat until all ingredients are in casserole.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Bake at 350°.

title: oreo delight
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Crush up all cookies with rolling pin.
Add cookies to butter (save 1/2 cup to garnish top of dessert).
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, cream the cheese; add milk and pudding, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of cookie crumbs.
Chill at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage. Set aside. Combine the rest of the ingredients. Put half of mixture unto greased 9x13 pan sprinkle with sausage. Cover with remaining potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with a salad.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter, 2 eggs, nuts and vanilla. Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then, mix cream cheese, sugar and 2 eggs.
Spread onto batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian chicken breasts
directions: Wash chicken breasts and pat dry.
Coat each breast in salad dressing.
Mix remaining ingredients and cover each piece of chicken.
Place in a shallow pan and bake in a 350°
oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until tender.

title: country coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion and carrots in a medium-size bowl.
In a small cup, combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour mayonnaise combination over cabbage and mix thoroughly.
Serves 2 to 4 people.

title: zucchini ground beef casserole
directions: Dissolve bouillon in hot water.
Add to stuffing mix.
Put stuffing on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook onion with hamburger. Add as next layer.
Cook other vegetables until tender; add as next layer.
Mix soup with 1/2 to 3/4 can water from cooked vegetables.
Spread on casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crete chicken and rice dish
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Saute onion, garlic and pepper until tender.
(Do not brown.)
Remove from pan.
Set aside.
Add chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on medium heat until done.
Remove from pan.
Set aside.
Drain water from peas into a pan.
Add 4 cups water and rice.
Cook until done.
Add all sauteed ingredients you set aside.
Stir well.
Top with chicken. Cover and heat all.
Serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and dice into cubes.
Drop into boiling salted water and cover pan.
Cook until potatoes are tender for about 20 minutes and drain.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together in a bowl.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until the mixture looks like coarse meal.
Add milk and stir until a dough forms. Turn out onto a lightly floured board or pastry cloth and knead about 20 kneading turns.
Pat dough out with hands to a thickness of 1/2 to 3/4-inch and cut with a 2 1/2 to 3-inch cutter.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet with sides touching and bake in a 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cajun crawfish etouffee(a la blanc)
directions: Melt butter in deep, thick pot (no black-iron).
Add onions, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute until soft.
Add crawfish; season to taste with hot sauce, if desired.
Smother on high fire, stirring constantly for about 20 minutes.
Add flour and continue smothering about 5 minutes.
Add parsley and onion tops (optional).
Add about 10 ounces of water (more or less) as needed.
If using tomato sauce, add now.
Cook about 15 minutes more on low simmer, covered.
Serve over hot rice with salad, potato salad and hot rolls or French bread.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry and blueberry truffle
directions: Mix pudding with skim milk and refrigerate until firm. Then add in 3 cups of light Cool Whip. Layer in truffle bowl (1) cube angel food cake, (2) strawberries, (3) blueberries, (4) pudding and Cool Whip mix and (5) light Cool Whip. Decorate top with strawberries and blueberries. Refrigerate at least 5 hours.

title: chili brie in sourdough
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine spices and sugar; set aside. Cut circle in top of bread and remove bread center to make room for Brie.
Spread butter in bread; sprinkle with 2 tsp. spice mixture.
With knife, make 2 inch cut around edge of bread at 1 inch intervals.
Remove rind from Brie and place in bread. Sprinkle
Brie with remaining spice.
Replace top of bread.
Bake on baking sheet 20 to 30 minutes.
To serve, remove bread top and break into bite size pieces.
Dip bread pieces in hot Brie.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss.
Store in tightly covered jar in refrigerator at least 24 hours.

title: hot sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and chop all ingredients finely.
Cook until thick.
Put into jars and seal.
Makes about 3 pints.

title: sunshine muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine eggs, water, milk and oil.
Stir in mixes; mix well.
Fill greased and floured muffin cups 1/2 full.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a mixer bowl, beat together cream cheese and powdered sugar until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and milk, beating until smooth and creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Turn into prepared pie crust.
Chill 5 or 6 hours or overnight.
May garnish with coarsely chopped peanuts.

title: waldorf apple salad
directions: Mix apples and avocado.
Moisten with lemon juice and stir well.
Add the other ingredients and chill.
Just before serving, place in a fruit bowl with lettuce.
Put on just enough mayonnaise to make the pieces of fruit stick together.
Decorate with a little shredded coconut.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: holiday fudge
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar.
Melt butter and chips together. Mix all the ingredients together and add vanilla and nuts.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted boiling water until tender; drain. Cook onion in 3 tablespoons butter until soft.
Stir in soup, salt, pepper and cheese.
Add carrots and place in 2-quart casserole. Toss stuffing with 1/3 cup melted butter; spoon over carrots.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Gut essa!

title: bar-be-cups
directions: Combine meat, sauce, onion and sugar. Press muffins into ungreased cupcake tin until cup is fully lined.
Spoon meat mixture into lined cups.
Sprinkle with Cheddar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: cinnamon and raisin biscuits
directions: Combine shortening with flour; mix until crumbly.
Gradually add buttermilk; mix very well.
Add raisins and cinnamon; mix completely.
Turn out onto floured board.
Knead about 10 times until smooth.
Cut out with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450°.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Put icing on biscuits while still warm.

title: orange oat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease bottoms of medium muffin pans with cooking spray.
Mix dry ingredients, add all other ingredients and mix until just moistened.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk well.
Add ice cream; mix well.
Pour into pie shell and top with Dream Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut. Chill until ready to eat (very good).

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Make 3 nests in this mixture. Put shortening, vanilla and vinegar (one in each nest).
Over all this, pour the water.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan until done.

title: christmas rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed in 2 cake pans.
Cool and poke holes with rod of wooden spoon.
Dissolve each flavor jello separately in 1 cup of boiling water and spoon red on 1 pan and green on other.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Dip 1 cake pan in warm water 10 seconds and remove to platter.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Dip other cake in warm water and set on top.
Frost entire cake with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with red and green sprinkles.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix egg, sugar and lemon juice. Heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
(For microwave, mix in a glass bowl and heat for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes at 70% power.)
Add flavorings and stir well.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Fold in whipped topping.
Serve with any kind of fruit pieces.

title: appetizer veggie pizzas
directions: Press dough onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread over baked dough.
Top with vegetables and sprinkle with cheese.
Cut into squares.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Combine all ingredients in small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture becomes thick.
Serves 2.

title: rice-consomme
directions: Saute onion in butter in baking dish.
Add rice and pour consomme over.
Bake
in 375° oven about 45 minutes.
Rice will absorb liquid and be lightly brown on top.	Yield: 5 servings.

title: 6 layer dinner
directions: Place ingredients in order given in layers in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper on each layer.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. These may be frozen before baking.

title: brine pickles
directions: Boil cider vinegar and pickling salt to dissolve salt.
Wash cucumbers.
Pack in sterile jars.
Pour mix over cucumbers.
Seal jars.
Don't put in wash or bath.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Place roast in a heavy pan.
Pour other ingredients over and bake for 5 hours at 300° to 350°.
Cook down if too much liquid.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crust:
Crush cookies; mix with 1/2 cup melted oleo.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: 25th anniversary salad
directions: Mix lemon jello according to package directions.
Let set a few minutes.
Add diced cream cheese and beat together.
Add pineapple; fold in marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put in large bowl and let set until firm.
Mix orange jello according to package directions; cool slightly and pour over first mixture while warm.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken in bite
size pieces and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In
separate	bowl,
mix
together both soups, tomatoes with chili
and
onion.
Pour
mixture
over chicken, cover with cheese and top generously with Doritos chips.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes;	uncovered the last 5 minutes.

title: pickled black-eyed peas
directions: Mix and put in a large jar or container with tight lid and refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
Stir gently occasionally.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chops and put into casserole dish. Sprinkle thyme and marjoram over each chop.
Place 1 ring of onion, pepper and tomato over each chop.
Pour uncooked rice around chops. Pour 1 can consomme soup and 1 can water over rice.
Cover casserole dish and place into 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: honey sweet potatoes
directions: Cool potatoes.
Slice in 1/2-inch pieces and add to sauce.

title: bran bread
directions: Place 1 cup
water in pan.
Add sugar and shortening.
Heat slowly until both are dissolved.
Add 2 cups tap water and set aside to cool.
Place 1 cup lukewarm water in large bowl. Sprinkle dry yeast on top.
Let sit until dissolved.
Add sugar and shortening mixture and All-Bran.
Stir in 3 to 4 cups flour. Add salt and about 7 more cups flour, stirring to make soft dough. Turn onto floured board and knead about 10 minutes.
Place in large greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Combine soup, dressing and preserves.
Mix until smooth. Place washed chicken in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: mexican tamales
directions: Lay tamales in a long, Pyrex dish.
Top tamales with above ingredients.
Set oven at 325° until bubbles in the middle.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in soup and milk.
Mix well.
Remove from heat and add tuna and pimento. Add cooked noodles and 1/2 cup cheese.
Put mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole dish and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook milk, sugar and butter for 2 minutes.

title: stewed corn and tomatoes
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Add onion and cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Add corn, tomatoes, pepper, salt and pepper, sugar and hot sauce.
Cook, covered, 20 minutes over medium-low heat until vegetables are tender.
Garnish with parsley and bacon; serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit.
Mix pudding with pineapple juice and Tang. Pour over fruit and let set in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal crispies(cookies)
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Stir in eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Sift flour with salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture. Add oats and raisins, chocolate chips or butterscotch chips to taste.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cal-tex casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown beef, breaking up with fork.
Add onion. Saute until tender.
Add salt, pepper and barbecue sauce.
Stir in beans.
Heat through.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix oleo, peanut butter and vanilla until smooth.
Add sugar gradually.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan that has been buttered.

title: bar-b-burgers
directions: Cook hamburger in oil.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper, chopped onion and green pepper, chili powder, tomato paste, can of water and barbecue sauce.
Simmer 1 hour, adding wine (juice) last 20 minutes of cooking.
Serve on hamburger buns with Irene's Slaw.

title: beef barley soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients except for frozen vegetables.
Cover; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 50 to 60 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add frozen vegetables and cook until tender.
Makes six quarts.
This soup freezes well.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix bread and milk together.
Add ground beef, seasonings and eggs.
Make into balls.
Fry, then simmer in 1 cup hot water and bouillon cube.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Scatter pineapple over fruit mixture.
Sprinkle dry cake mix in a layer over the filling.
Drop slices of margarine over the cake mix.
Scatter nuts and coconut on top.
(Do not stir.)
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cake is done and lightly browned.

title: kaye's relish
directions: Prepare vegetables and set aside.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar and bring to a boil; add salt and pepper.
Pour liquid over vegetables and let sit over night.
Drain before serving.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Bring margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa to a rolling boil in saucepan.
Boil for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Let stand to cool.

title: macaroni, sausage and peppers
directions: Brown sausage with green peppers.
Remove excess oil.
Add sauce and simmer 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni as directed and add to sauce mixture.
Ready to serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil and mash potatoes until smooth.
Mix with rest of ingredients and
cool.
Put into greased casserole.
Refrigerate overnight to room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Dot with butter and sprinkle paprika.
Works great to put in crock-pot.

title: gumbo sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Mix
cake
mix	and bake as directed.
When cake cools, cut into small squares.
Mix instant pudding mix with milk.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt and milk. Blend well and add dry ingredients; mix well.
After completely mixed, add 1 cup boiling water.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onions; add tomatoes and tomato soup thinned with 2 cups water and simmer slowly for 2 hours.
Add celery, carrots, green pepper, salt, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Add chopped noodles and cook 1 hour longer.
If too thick, add water.

title: southern style creamed corn
directions: Melt
butter.
Stir
in
flour,
sugar
and salt.
After ingredients are mixed well, add milk slowly continuing to stir. Add
corn.
Serve
warm.
According to your preference, you may want to add more milk to thin it out a little.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown ground chuck, onions and green pepper.
Drain, add garlic powder, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer until liquid evaporates.
Add tomatoes, chili beans and cubed cheese.
Melt over low heat, stirring to keep from burning.
Serve over tortilla chips.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dump crushed pineapple into ungreased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread evenly over bottom.
Dump cherry pie filling over pineapple and spread evenly.
Dump yellow cake mix over fruit and level off with a spoon.
Cut butter into pats and spread evenly over top of cake mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: boiled or cooked salad dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add water and vinegar mixture.
Add well beaten eggs.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat and add butter.
When ready to use, can be thinned with cream or whipped cream to desired consistency. Can also thin with a little Miracle Whip.
Can be used with bean or potato salad.
Keeps well in fridge.

title: lemon dill chicken saute
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a shallow dish. Dip chicken in egg and dredge in crumb mixture. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add chicken and cook 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
Feeds 4.

title: quick chicken meal
directions: Bring full pan of water to boil with chicken and onion; boil until chicken is done.
Take a box of rice or 1/2 of 2 pound box of rice and dump into water with chicken.
Mix salt and pepper to taste; put in 3 tablespoons basil leaves and cook until rice is done.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease generously and flour 4 coffee cans.
Pour a little hot water over 1 cup raisins (let set to be drained before use).
Beat together the eggs and Crisco oil; add water and pumpkin.
Mix well the following together: sugar (white and brown), flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and instant pudding mix.
Combine dry ingredients with first 4 ingredients, already mixed.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drain raisins and put in. Mix and divide in 4 (1 pound) coffee cans, filling 1/2 full.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be served plain or with the following topping.

title: almond hershey torte
directions: Crush vanilla wafers into fine crumbs.
Sprinkle 1/2 of crumbs in bottom of 8 1/2 x 11-inch loaf pan.
Melt chocolate bar and marshmallows with milk in top of double boiler.
Cool.
Thoroughly whip cream until firm.
Fold in cooled chocolate mix.
Spread over crumbs and sprinkle remaining crumbs and almonds on top.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine, then add milk. Blend until smooth. Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Mix all together.
Add peas, almonds and pimento. Separate 8 crescent dinner rolls into 4 rectangles. Seal perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup mixture into middle. Fold up and seal sides.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4.

title: clams casino
directions: Using bacon drippings or vegetable oil, saute celery, onions and pepper until soft.
Add water.
Salt and pepper to taste and allow to simmer for 15 minutes (if any mixture leftover, freeze). Open clams (top of neck) and leave on half shell.
Cover clams with mixture.
Cover mixture with slice of sharp cheese.
Cover cheese with portion of raw bacon.
Place in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until cooked.

title: highland shortbread
directions: Cream butter and gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and salt; add to creamed mixture.
(Add more flour if needed to make dough easy to handle.) Shape dough into 3/4 inch balls; place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Gently press a pecan half in the center of each.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Yields: 6 dozen.

title: spaghetti
directions: In medium pot (sprayed with Pam), brown meat and push to one side.
In same pot, add onion and green pepper; cook until tender. Mix meat, veggies, tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Add remaining ingredients (except spaghetti).
In another pot, boil spaghetti noodles according to package directions.
Serve spaghetti sauce on bed of spaghetti noodles.
Add Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Serve with garlic bread and tossed salad.
Enjoy!

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Form into a loaf. Reserve one-half can tomato sauce.
Pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put cut up chicken in casserole dish.
Mix soup and broth; pour over chicken.
Mix Bisquick and sweet milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: turtles
directions: Place open can of Eagle Brand milk in boiling water for 3 hours.
Melt chocolate bars in double boiler.
Pour small amount of chocolate in bottom of nut cup.
Place pecans on top of chocolate. Pour cooked Eagle Brand on top of pecans.
Top with chocolate.

title: devil dogs
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Beat next 3 ingredients together.
To egg mixture, add cooking oil.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.

title: conch chowder
directions: Saute onion and salt pork until brown.
Add potatoes, tomatoes and enough water to cover.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add conch, seasonings, hot sauce and sherry, if desired.

title: strawberry sour cream mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir until strawberries are melted.
Add pineapple and juice.
Place half the mixture in a mold.
Let set in refrigerator, then spread over the 1 cup sour cream carefully.
Pour over remaining half of jello mixture.
Allow to set at least 4 to 5 hours.

title: raspberry-blueberry salad
directions: Layer 1:
Dissolve 1 box Jell-O in a dish and let set.

title: squash or eggplant casserole
directions: Cook squash or eggplant until mushy and drain.
Add all other ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese, crumbs and small amount of oleo.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese, crumbs and oleo.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly and well set and slightly brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken with broth and soup. Mix bisquick and add milk. Pour soup mix in a 12 X 13 baking dish. Pour bisquick over soup mix. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour or until brown and bubbly.

title: fruit smoothies
directions: Combine the bananas, fresh fruit and juice. Add a couple of ice cubes and blend.
May add honey, and/or cinnamon and vanilla.

title: hay and straw
directions: Cook the pasta per package instructions. Put oil and garlic in pan and cook together for about 5 minutes. Add sausage and brown. Drain sausage grease. Return to hot pan which should have about 1/4 cup milk, 2 tablespoons butter and cooked pasta. Mix until butter is melted. Add 1 cup Parmesan. Serve.

title: saucy pickles
directions: Drain all the juice from the pickles. Mix sugar, garlic and Tabasco sauce. Return the pickles to the jar alternating layers with sugar mixture. Let stand for 3 days, turning over each day. Sugar mixture should be completely dissolved.
They are sweet and hot!

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk.

title: margaret's sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts in margarine.
After turning chicken to brown second side, cover pan with lid and cook chicken on low for 20 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add green pepper and onion to pan drippings and saute.
Add cornstarch and pineapple with juice. Add chicken, which has been cubed, and continue cooking 5 minutes. Serve over chow mein noodles.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Yields 3 servings.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it will spin a thread from the spoon.
Cool 5 minutes.
Pour slowly into egg whites as you beat together.
Spoon on wax paper.

title: pineapple cream cheese squares
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and the butter.
Press into the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes. Cool.

title: pork flavored green beans
directions: Place beans, bacon drippings, ham bone, salt and pepper in
5 quart saucepot.
Add water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to low heat; cover and cook for 1 hour.	Makes 10 servings.

title: best rum cake ever(read carefully before starting.)
directions: Before starting, sample rum; check for quality.
Test again if in doubt.
Now start.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the rum quality again; it must be just right.
To be sure rum is of the highest quality, pour into a large glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat.
With the electric mixer, beat 1 cup of butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add one seaspoon of thugar; beat again.
Meanwhile, make sure rum is of quiest holity. Try another cup.
Open 2nd quart if necessary.
Add 2 arge leggs and 2 cups fried druit and beat until high.
If druit gets stuck in beater, pry it loose with a drew scriver.
Sample rum again, testing for tonscicticity.
Next, sift 3 cups of pepper or salt. Sample rum again.
Sift half pint of lemon juice; fold in chopped butter and strained nuts.
Add one babblespoon of brown thugar or any color.
Mix well.
Grease oven and turn cake pan to 350°.
Pour all into coven and ake.
Check rum and bo to ged.

title: pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add oil and sugar.
Sift and add the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in zucchini, pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: ranch style crackers
directions: Mix dressing mix with oil; stir well.
Place crackers in airtight container. Pour oil and dressing mixture over the crackers and shake.
Leave for at least 24 hours, shaking every now and then.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Cook onion.
Mix all ingredients (except almonds) together.
Top with slivered almonds.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk until forms soft ball.
Add chocolate bits and stir until melted.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Add as many nuts as you wish.
Spread in buttered pans.

title: old-fashioned fried pies
directions: Prepare fruit as follows:
Cover with water and cook in covered saucepan until done. Add sugar and spices to taste and a tad of butter or oleo. Set aside.

title: quick lamb curry
directions: Coat skillet with no stick cooking spray.
Brown onion while you slice apples.
Add apples and raisins to skillet and brown lightly.
Add water and curry powder.
Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Add lamb.
Continue to cook for 5 minutes.
Add peanuts and stir.
Remove from heat for a minute.
Then serve with rice.
Each person takes assorted condiments to mix with individual bites of curry.
Makes 4 servings.

title: appetizer pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Stir in dried beef, onion, green pepper and pepper.
Mix well; add sour cream.
Spoon into an 8-inch pie plate or shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot as spread on crackers.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute and slowly turn half of mixture into egg yolks.
Then beat into hot mixture in saucepan and boil 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, continue stirring until smooth. Blend in lime juice and grated lime rind and food coloring.
Pour into shell, top with meringue.
Bake in 400° oven for about 10 minutes, until meringue browns.
Cool away from draft.

title: cool fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and marshmallow cream.
Mix thoroughly. Serve with sliced fruit or wafer cookies.

title: frozen fruit cake
directions: Scald milk.
Blend sugar, flour and salt.
Add to milk.
Cook 10 minutes.
Pour over beaten eggs.
Cook until thick.
Chill and add vanilla.
Add other ingredients, folding in whipped cream last.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes prior to serving.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown turkey and onion and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat until thoroughly warm.

title: baked yellow squash
directions: Cook squash.
Drain and mash well.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: coconut creme delight
directions: Mix crushed crackers with melted butter and line 9 x 13-inch pan with cracker mixture.
Save 1/2 cup of cracker mixture for topping.
Refrigerate crust.
Mix softened ice cream and pudding and milk with mixer; pour over crust.
Spread Cool Whip over ice cream mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cracker mixture on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes or until done.
Will be golden brown.

title: zonkers popcorn
directions: Fold mixture until well coated and spread on surface until dry.
Makes lots and is addictive!

title: chilled herb shrimp
directions: Shell and clean shrimp, leaving tails intact.
In a medium saucepan, place shrimp and Worcestershire sauce; bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until shrimp turn pink, 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients and chill.
Drain and serve. Garnish with additional fresh herbs, if desired.

title: scrunch
directions: Mix together the cereals, morsels and nuts. Set aside. Stirring constantly in a saucepan, combine syrup, sugar and butter. Bring to a boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Cool 10 minutes over cereal mixture all at once. Toss to coat evenly. Cool 15 minutes, then shape as desired.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add butter, milk, eggs and cheese. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spread in buttered 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika and an additional 1/3 cup shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Pour the pistachio pudding in a bowl and add crushed pineapple plus the juice, marshmallows, nuts and Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: garlic-buttered mushrooms
directions: Mix butter, shallot, garlic, parsley, cheese and pepper until well blended. Twist off mushroom stems. Evenly spoon butter mixture into mushroom caps.
Place mushrooms on a rack in a broiler pan about 6-inches below heat.
Cook until butter is melted and mushrooms begin to shrivel slightly (about 5 minutes). Serve on bread slices to absorb buttery juices.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries; save to make Jell-O. Add enough water to juice to make one pint.
Boil to make Jell-O. When Jell-O begins to set, add pineapple, cherries, nuts and raisins.
Warm cream cheese and mix with mayonnaise.
Spread on salad.
This salad is great for Christmas.

title: sauteed zucchini
directions: Saute onions in hot oil until tender.
Add next 5 ingredients. Cook over low heat 7 minutes or until zucchini is tender. Sprinkle with cheese and serve immediately.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 8-inch round cake pan; stir in brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple rings in cake pan.
(Place whole slice in center, surround with half slices.) Lightly beat egg in mixing bowl.
Add milk and muffin mix; stir just until blended.
Spread batter over pineapple.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Turn out onto serving plate immediately.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Into a large bowl, mix flour, baking powder and soda.
Add butter and blend with fork or fingers until resembling coarse corn meal.
Add sugar, salt, raisins and nutmeg; mix same.
Then add whipped eggs and buttermilk and knead only long enough to form cake.
Cut cross on top and bake in preheated oven (350°) for 40 minutes.

title: chinese stewed chicken
directions: Put stewing sauce and 4 cups water in pot big enough to hold chicken. Bring to boil. Add chicken and turn heat to low. Cover and cook at low heat for 10 minutes. Turn the chicken over and simmer 10 more minutes. Turn off heat. Allow chicken to stand in sauce for 20 minutes. Remove and drain. Let cool. Sprinkle with sesame oil and serve.

title: walnut crown pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 or 10-inch angel pan.
Spread walnuts over bottom.
Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Add milk, shortening and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add unbeaten eggs.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Pour over walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easy italian love cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Prepare cake mix as directed; set aside in baking pan.
In a separate bowl, with mixer at medium speed, blend Ricotta cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Spoon mixture over unbaked cake batter; do not mix.
Bake for 1 hour (or until cake tester comes out dry). Cool on rack.
Frost with Frosting for Italian Love Cake.

title: chris' chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Put chicken in a large saucepan with 3 cups water, 1 teaspoon salt and a few peppercorns or black pepper. Bring to boiling; lower heat. Cover. Simmer 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender. Drain. Debone. Cut meat into bite-size pieces. You should have about 2 cups. Place uncut sausage in 350° oven for 10 minutes. Remove and slice into bite-size pieces. Saut onions, garlic, celery and green pepper in margarine. Combine chicken, sausage, rice, consomm and all other ingredients in a heavy pot with tight fitting cover. Bring to boiling; lower heat. Cover. Simmer at lowest heat for 1 hour. Do not remove cover at any time during cooking. Serves 6 to 10.

title: orange candy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy large kettle.
Boil until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add orange candy melt and marshmallow cream.
Stir this up.
Add orange flavoring.
Stir well.
Pour into a large buttered cookie sheet.

title: never-fail chocolate fudge
directions: Put chocolate drops, margarine and vanilla in a large bowl. In a saucepan put sugar, milk and salt.
Let this come to a rolling boil (while stirring) and boil for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour over chocolate drops.
Stir until chocolate has melted and mixed real well.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts (or more) and pour in a large pan that has been greased with margarine.
Let set until cold and cut in squares.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: hot bacon and swiss dip
directions: Blend all together and put in glass pie pan.
Microwave until cheese melts. Serve with Triscuits or breadsticks.

title: scarlet daiquiri
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.

title: bananas royale
directions: In medium skillet combine brown sugar, Crisco, half and half, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils.
Boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add sliced bananas, stirring gently to coat.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes or until soft, stirring occasionally.
Stir in brandy.
Serve over ice cream.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: reuben quiche
directions: Squeeze small handfuls of sauerkraut to extract all moisture. Saute kraut in butter in skillet until it begins to brown and is covered in butter.
Add caraway seed.
Put kraut in prepared pie shell.
Top with corned beef; top that with cheese slices.
Pour custard of milk and eggs over everything.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, or until custard is set.
Serves 4 adults.

title: cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly margarine, sugar, egg and flavoring.
Add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Cover dough and chill 2 to 3 hours. Roll dough 1/8 inch thick.
Cut.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: banana pie
directions: Use only 2 3/4 cups milk for each package pudding.
This will make the pudding set better to slice.

title: beefy mexican dip
directions: Melt cheese in chili in small saucepan. Add green chili peppers and jalapeno peppers to taste.
Serve warm with corn chips or nachos.
Preparation time:
5 minutes.
Cooking time:
10 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice and let stand 10 minutes.
Melt oil and butter in skillet.
Add garlic, onion, m.s.g., salt and pepper; brown lightly.
Add ham and shrimp.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add rice.
Toss. Add ketchup.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Serve with soy sauce.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Blend cake mix and pudding.
Add milk and oil.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat 4 minutes all together.
Stir in 1 package chocolate chips.
Put German chocolate bar, grated, in cake mix.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour (50 minutes), in a Bundt cake pan.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring to a boil the first 3 ingredients.
Let simmer 1 hour. Add the brandy, vodka and vanilla. Bottle in dark bottles, if available.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add 2 cups flour with salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add remaining flour.
Mix dough and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Make dough into small balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Press down with fork. Bake at 350° until done.
Cookies will not be brown.

title: cookie bars
directions: Add egg, oil and water to cake mix.
You may add nuts, raisins, coconut or chocolate chips; most anything goes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet, or just spread the whole thing out in a pan and bake, then cut into bars.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, if done in pan.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Mix nuts, jello and coconut in a bowl. Stir in milk, vanilla and food coloring. Chill overnight. Shape into strawberries, about 1 teaspoonful, then roll in more dry jello. Add green stem with cake icing.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions.
Combine all ingredients.
Cover with Pepperidge Farm chicken stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 people.

title: snack (small mini pizza)
directions: Place crackers on cookie sheet.
Put about 1 teaspoon of sauce on each cracker, then place pepperoni and then a small piece of Swiss cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 400° until cheese melts.

title: cinnamon sugar cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter, sugars and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and cream of tartar.
Stir in the pecans (if desired). Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet; flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Sprinkle with colored sugar (if desired).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
8 dozen.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate 30 minutes before serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to boil 1 minute.
Add 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add 2 1/2 to 3 cups oatmeal.

title: christmas wreath cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed of mixer until creamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Mix well.
Add flour and orange juice alternately.

title: greek salad
directions: Rub a large salad bowl with the cut garlic clove.
Place romaine, radishes, olives, onion, green pepper, cucumber and tomato in bowl.
Add black pepper, dill, oregano and vinegar.
Toss.
Add olive oil and toss again.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all and set in refrigerator overnight or several hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together. Pour into 9 x 13 greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients
together and bake in three 8-inch pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: sesame seed brittle
directions: Toast sesame seed on a large baking sheet at 350° for about 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and butter in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Reduce heat and cook without stirring until mixture reaches the hard crack stage (300° on the candy thermometer).
Remove from heat; stir in sesame seed and soda.
Pour onto a greased surface and spread evenly to about 1/8-inch thickness.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
Yield:
About 1 1/2 pounds.

title: nancy's potato salad dressing
directions: Whisk all ingredients together.

title: banana pudding
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Slowly stir in flour until blended.
Add sugars, beaten
eggs and milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture bubbles and begin to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Layer pudding with vanilla wafer cookies and sliced bananas.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan:
crushed pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Cream together cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Fold the Cool Whip into the cream cheese and spread on pretzel mixture.
Dissolve the strawberry Jell-O into 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in the 2 packages of strawberries. When slightly thick, pour on cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: that cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, mix together the cake mix, margarine, one of the eggs and nuts.
Spread the mixture in bottom of pan.
In a separate bowl, mix together the powdered sugar, the remaining 2 eggs and the cream cheese.
Spread over the mixture in pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Cool before cutting into squares.
This cake will not look done when you remove from oven, but will be okay after it has cooled.

title: snicker salad
directions: Mix all together, except marshmallows.
May add marshmallows now.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add the 3 cans of beans. Add barbecue sauce and water.
Let simmer for 1 hour.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry nut salad
directions: Mix cherries and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add cherry jello. Let this mixture cool for approximately 5 minutes.
Add nuts.
Put in refrigerator to congeal.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Form in loaf.
Lay slices of bacon across top and bake in moderate oven (375°) 2 hours.
If desired substitute 1/2 cup uncooked oat cereal for 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Serve with tomato sauce (if desired).

title: hunt's macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine oil and flour in skillet; heat and stir together. Add tomato sauce, onion, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add macaroni and cheese; mix well.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, to keep from sticking.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage head.
Cook in water until tender; drain.
Melt butter and add onion.
Cook until soft.
Add cheese, soup and bread cubes and mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350°, uncovered.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, mixing well. Then add next 5 ingredients.
Pour half of the batter into a greased Bundt cake pan.
Combine nuts, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle half the cinnamon mixture over the batter.
Pour the rest of the batter on top and then sprinkle again with the remaining nut mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Then add flour, cream of tartar, baking powder.
Blend both mixtures together well.
Chill dough for about one hour.
Form into balls and flatten with a glass dipped in flour.
(Dip the glass in the flour for each cookie).
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in 350 oven for 10-15 minutes or until cookies are delicate brown.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Add water to Jell-O. Stir and set aside 1/4 cup mixture.

Add pineapple (juice and all). Mix well. Set in refrigerator to gel. Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; set aside. Whip Dream Whip. Mix with cream cheese mixture and 1/4 cup Jell-O mixture. Spread on top of congealed Jell-O. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: tuna balls
directions: Combine and form into balls.
Chill before serving.

title: lemon congealed salad
directions: Mix together jello, water and marshmallows.
Place in refrigerator until thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Top with extra marshmallows.
(Any flavor jello may be used.)

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on.
Boil eggs; cool both.
