Peel off skins and dice potatoes into large bowl.
Shell the eggs and dice into bowl.
Chop onion, pepper and celery and put into bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar and salt with enough milk to dissolve them; add mustard and stir until well blended. Pour over potatoes, eggs, onion, pepper and celery.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: herbed pork roast
directions: In a large oven cooking bag or resealable bag combine the first eight ingredients.
Add roast, seal and turn to coat.
Place bag in a shallow roasting pan.
Refrigerate over night, turning bag several times.
If using a cooking bag, make several slits in top of bag.
If not remove roast from plastic bag and place in roasting pan.
Pour marinade over roast, cover pan and bake at 350 degrees for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours
or until thermometer reads 160 degrees.
Serves 6 to 8.
I leave mine in the frig for a couple of days it increases the flavor.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix everything in bowl, except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 in a mold;
set.
Spread
the
sour
cream over mixture.
Add the rest of the Jell-O mixture that is partly thick.
Do not drain strawberries or
crushed pineapple.
You can put sour cream on the top when it is set.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, melt the butter in the oven; remove.
In bowl, beat the eggs, add flour, milk, salt and baking powder; mix well.
Add cheese and spinach and blend.
Pour into buttered pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Remove and cool 10 minutes to set.
Cut into bite-size squares. Can freeze by placing squares on cookie sheet, freeze solid.
Place in plastic bag and store.
To serve, heat 12 minutes at 325°. Preparation:
15 minutes.
Baking:
35 minutes.
Easy.
Can do ahead.
Yields 32 squares.
Can freeze.

title: mexi-burger
directions: Place meat and vegetables in a kettle.
Add water to smooth consistency.
Add the spices.
Heat through to a simmer for 1/2 hour.
May be served as a sauce on hot dogs or as a barbecue sandwich.

title: low-fat granola
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In large mixing bowl, combine oats, almonds and wheat germ.
Mix the honey and apple juice together and pour over oat mixture.
Stir oat mixture until coated.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Spread oat mixture evenly in pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until brown. Stir every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir in raisins and dried fruit.
Transfer mixture to another pan and cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: marian fruit salad
directions: Drain cherries, peaches, pears and pineapple thoroughly and combine in a large bowl.
Blend together remaining ingredients. Fold into fruit.
Chill overnight.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: lemon blueberry jello
directions: Mix jello packages and hot water until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Stir in pie filling and lemon juice.
Mix well. Refrigerate until set.
Spread Cool Whip before serving.
For a different taste, change flavors of jello and pie filling.

title: sirloin strips saute
directions: Brown strips in oil.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Stir.
Five minutes later, add broccoli.
Combine bouillon cubes and hot water and then add to mixture.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and cold water.
Add to mixture to thicken.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Serve with rice.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add oil, cinnamon, salt, vanilla and zucchini.
Mix well.
In separate bowl, mix flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Then add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in two loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: By hand, mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 250° to 300° for about one hour.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix chillies, cheese and dressing in mixer.
Spread on shells (thick).
Roll up and chill for 1 hour.
Then slice in pinwheels.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Rough chop artichokes.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Then, take the bread and cut a 4-inch square on top and cut to the bottom but don't cut all the way through.
Hollow out completely under and to the sides.
Fill cavity with dip.
Wrap bread in foil, leaving the top where the dip is exposed. Bake in 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Then, pull foil off and brown the bread. Serve hot.

title: marshmallow peanut fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk in a saucepan.
Cook to soft-ball stage (234°).
Add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a buttered pan about 9 x 9-inches.
Cool and cut in squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Put 1/2 of crumbs on the bottom of a buttered casserole dish.
Pour in squash mixture.
Top with remaining crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Bake in lightly greased angel food cake pan.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not open oven!

title: catfish supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place catfish, skin side up, in a glass oven dish, side by side.
Sprinkle lightly with coarse pepper and drizzle 1 tablespoon of oil over filets.
Meanwhile, saute all vegetables in 1 tablespoon oil, using a large skillet until almost done.
Then sprinkle sesame seed over vegetables and cook until lightly brown.
After 15 minutes of cooking, remove catfish from oven and spread vegetables equally over each filet.
Serve with salad and white or red wine.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix all ingredients except carrots.
Peel carrots and cut very thin.
Pour over the marinade and let it sit overnight or longer. Drain the carrots before serving.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix with hands and form into eggs.
Chill or freeze until firm.
Dip in chocolate.

title: "a better chicken casserole"
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water until tender.
Steam broccoli until tender.
Mix soup, curry powder, lemon juice and mayonnaise with sliced mushrooms.
Spread cut-up broccoli in bottom of well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove bones from chicken and cut up into 1-inch pieces; spread over broccoli.
Pour soup mixture over all and cover with cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs combined with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be assembled in advance.
Just refrigerate and then bake.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Melt Cheez Whiz over low heat. Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: gluhwein
directions: Boil all ingredients together, except the wine and reduce by half.
Strain and add wine.
Bring to a boil.
Serve hot.

title: mexican cornbread meat dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat lightly.
Drain and set aside.
Mix cornmeal, soda, salt, eggs, milk and corn.
Heat large iron skillet (about 11-inch) on burner with about 1/8 to 1/4 cup oil until hot.
Add 1/2 cornmeal mixture to pan.
Layer meat, onion, peppers and cheese.
Top this with other 1/2 of cornmeal mixture.
Cook in oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with green beans or pot of red beans and a salad.

title: wild rice and chicken casserole
directions: Drain mushrooms; reserve liquid.
Prepare rice according to package directions.
Saute onion in butter in a skillet until transparent.
Blend in flour.
Stir in chicken broth and reserved mushroom liquid, gradually.
Add cream.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients except almonds; mix well.
Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate honey bun cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Grease bottom only of 9x13 pan. Beat cake mix, water, oil, eggs and sour cream in bowl with electric mixer on medium speed for one minute. Spread half of batter in pan. Mix brown sugar, pecans, chocolate chips and cinnamon, sprinkle over batter in pan. Drop remaining batter evenly over pecan mixture, carefully spread to cover. Bake for 55-60 minutes. Prick surface of warm cake several times with a fork. Spread frosting over warm cake. Frosting will be very thin. Cool completely.

title: georgia pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, corn syrup, melted butter, vanilla and chopped pecans to the beaten eggs.
Pour into an uncooked pie shell and cook in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes, or until set as custard.

title: pretzel-strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 6 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool completely.
In a bowl, beat cream cheese; add 1 cup sugar and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix jello, water and strawberries.
Let cool slightly.
Pour over cheese mixture; refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: glazed carrots
directions: In a
quart microwave safe casserole combine carrots and 2 tablespoons water.
Cook, covered, on 100% power (High) 5 to 7 minutes
or
until crisp-tender.
Drain and set aside. For glaze in a 1 cup glass measure combine orange juice, brown sugar, cornstarch
and
salt.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 30 seconds to 1
minutes or until thickened and bubbly; stir every 30 seconds.
Add margarine and honey; stir until melted. Pour over carrots; toss.

title: croatian pita
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla; add remaining ingredients except apples.
Combine apples with sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Roll half of dough about 1/2 inch thick.
Place in greased pan.
Cover with sliced and sweetened apple slices.
Roll out other half of dough and cover.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix all in a bowl.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all together.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill before cutting.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all together.
Use 3 to 4 heaping teaspoons per mug of hot water.

title: winter white chili
directions: In large saucepan, brown meat in oil with cumin, onion, chili powder and white pepper.
Stir in corn, broth and chilies.
Bring to a boil;
cover and simmer 15-20 minutes. Add beans until hot. Top with cheese.

title: creamed tuna casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, except chips.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: no cholesterol noodle pudding
directions: Combine cottage cheese, apples, raisins and undrained pineapple.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Place 1/3 of cooked noodles in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 of cheese mixture and 1/3 of cinnamon mixture.
Layer again 1/3 of noodles, 1/2 of cheese and 1/3 of cinnamon.
End with remaining noodles and brush with margarine.
Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine the dry ingredients. Gradually add to the creamed mixture (batter will be very firm). Shape into 48 balls, about 1-inch round, and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Push one cherry halfway into each ball.
Make frosting.

title: cherry jello
directions: Use the pineapple juice and juice from the cherries added to the water needed to mix jello.
Add the pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes.
Cut round slices approximately 1/2-inch thick.
Cook until done.
Do not stir.
Do not pour water off.
Let potatoes cool completely before draining water, they will mush if you do.
Mix soup and cheese chunks in microwave bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir; microwave 2 more minutes and stir. Do this until cheese melts.
Add evaporated milk to thin to desired consistency.
Pour over drained potatoes.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour and soda over eggs.
Add fruit cocktail and beat with spoon.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in oblong pan.

title: chinese cake
directions: Pour all ingredients into mixing bowl.
Mix by hand.
Do not use mixer.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Let bread dough rise, roll dough out in a rectangle and layer with a base of butter, then ham, salami, cheese, pepperoni, peppers, onions and mushrooms.
Bring sides together and ends. Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 425°.
Baste with butter occasionally.
Top with your favorite spaghetti sauce.

title: irish stew
directions: In a heavy saucepan, arrange alternate layers of vegetables and meat with just enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until all is tender.
Shake pan now and then to prevent sticking.
Serves 4.

title: lazy piroghies
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions, rinse and drain well. Melt oleo in saucepan.
Slice onions in oleo.
Cook until soft. Add mushroom soup (undiluted), mushrooms (including liquid) and sauerkraut which has been rinsed and drained well.
Heat until hot.
Add to macaroni and mix well.

title: beef cubes in wine
directions: Brown beef.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours. Serve with rice or noodles.

title: skillet toasted nuts
directions: Use halves or pieces of walnuts, almonds, Brazil nuts or pecans. Saute nuts in butter,
margarine or salad oil, allowing 2 tablespoons fat for each cup of nuts until nicely toasted and crunchy.
About 5 minutes.
Drain on paper toweling, sprinkling with salt if desired.
Nice on cakes, frostings, etc.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and seasonings. Add to shrimp and vegetables. Mix lightly. Chill. Serve in lettuce cup.

title: peach pickles
directions: Mix together all ingredients except peaches.
Bring to a boil, drop peaches into the mixture and cook until tender.
Put into jars with some of the liquid and seal.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add flour and sugar; remove from heat.
Add sour cream; mix with beans and mushrooms. Melt remaining butter; mix with crushed Ritz crackers.
Cover casserole with cheese.
Top with cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peach custard cake
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan.
Mix flour, salt and margarine. Spread in pan. Drain peaches, but save 1/2 cup of the syrup. Arrange peaches on crust in pan. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix 1/2 cup peach syrup, egg and Carnation milk.
Pour over peaches. Bake at 350° until custard is firm.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: fruit slush
directions: Fill ring 1/3 full of water and white grape juice; partially freeze.
Arrange and press lemon slices, strawberries and mint leaves into ice.
Freeze until garnish is fixed in place.
Gently fill mold with additional water-grape juice and freeze solid. Before serving, unmold ice ring and place fruit side up into punch bowl.
Add punch.

title: fred kahle's fish dish
directions: Combine all ingredients, except fish.
Cut fish into 4 pieces. Place on top of rice in a casserole dish.
Cover with foil. Place in a 350° oven.
Bake for 30 or 40 minutes, until fish is flake-tender.

title: broccoli, rice and chicken
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ellen's peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water until it forms a hard ball or spins an 8 or 10-inch thread.
Use a candy thermometer for best results. Then add peanuts and cook until peanuts are light golden brown (they will begin to make a slight popping sound) and syrup turns a golden brown.
Add soda and vanilla.
Stir quickly, then pour into 3 greased cookie sheets.
Butter your fingers and stretch candy by pulling at the edges.
Be very careful, because it is very hot. Let cool, then break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute all ingredients, except seasonings in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add seasonings and simmer.
Mash ingredients until smooth.
Add 2 cups milk and 1 cup shredded cheese.
Stir until melted.
Serve hot.

title: layered chili cheese dip
directions: In a microwavable pie pan, warm cream cheese until spreadable. Spread over bottom of pie pan.
Place refried beans on cream cheese and microwave until warm.
Spread refried beans to cover cream cheese.
Place chili on refried beans and microwave until warm.
Spread chili to cover refried beans.
Cover with shredded cheese and microwave to melt.
Sprinkle with black olives (if desired) and serve warm with nacho chips.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: Add liquid to the cucumbers.
Let set overnight.
Bring to a boil again.
Let stand at room temperature.
Bring to a boil again.
Put in jars and seal.
If liquid runs low add a little water.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add sour cream.
Separate eggs; add yolks to cream.
Add flour, soda and vanilla.
Mix well. Add beaten egg whites and mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Make an ice ring of 7-Up.
If punch bowl is large enough, you can double the recipe.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together well; stir in egg.
Add buttermilk until pourable consistency.
Pour into iron skillet with hot bacon drippings; heat on high for about 30 seconds.
Put in a 400° oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Cook very slowly without stirring until it forms a ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from fire; add butter and cool before beating.

title: shrimp arnaud
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate for 24 hours.
Serve on crackers as an appetizer.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend together all ingredients.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake in a 375° (moderate) oven, until knife inserted near center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes. Cool, refrigerate at least 1 hour.
This pie is easy to make, we had it often as a kid.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of coloring and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk with salt, alternately with flour and vanilla.
Last: add soda, baking powder and vinegar.
Bake in two 9-inch pans, greased and lightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hungarian stew
directions: Saute onions over low heat until golden brown, then add beef and stir for 10 minutes. Toss in paprika.
Add 1 cup warm water. Cover and cook 1 hour over low heat.
Add more water, if necessary.
After about 45 minutes, add peeled tomatoes, cut into 1-inch pieces, pepper rings and salt.
Cook until tender.

title: date coconut balls
directions: Melt butter or margarine. Beat eggs. Add sugar and stir into melted butter.
Add dates.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes slowly, stirring constantly.
Add Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
Let cool.
Make into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: onion soup
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onions in margarine 25 minutes covered and 5 minutes uncovered.
Add parsley the last 5 minutes.
Blend.
Add beef broth and mix well.
Serve piping hot.

title: old-fashioned meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight in refrigerator. Next day, shape into a loaf and put in a baking dish.
Cover with thin layer of catsup.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 15 people.

title: zucchini-carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until frothy.
Gradually beat in oil. Add dry ingredients.
Beat at high speed, for about 4 minutes. Stir in carrots, zucchini
and 1/2 cup nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 35 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
Top springs back when touched.
Make a cream cheese frosting.

title: butterscotch pie filling
directions: In large skillet, melt butter; add brown sugar and 1/2 cup milk.
Cook to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Cook additional 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
In small bowl, add egg yolks, 2 cups milk, flour and salt.
Add to the mixture in the skillet.
Stir constantly, cooking until thick.
Add vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar with butter.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in bananas and lemon juice.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add and mix in quickly.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool on rack.

title: turkey chili
directions: In a large pan over medium heat, cook green pepper and onion in salad oil until tender.
Stir in chili powder.
Cook 1 minute. Stir in tomatoes, kidney beans, turkey, sugar, salt and crushed red pepper over high heat.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer at least 10 minutes to blend flavors, stirring occasionally. Serve in bowls with cheese and chips if desired.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Cook beef with chopped onion.
Mix all together and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or cornbread.

title: peaches 'n pears cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, pudding mix, baking powder, salt, egg, milk and butter in a mixing bowl.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch deep dish pie plate. Drain peaches and pears.
Reserve juice.
Arrange fruit decoratively on top of the batter.

title: hot tomato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix Ro-Tel tomatoes with soup.
Crush tortilla chips slightly.
Layer ingredients in a two-quart casserole dish, beginning and ending with chips.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: Whip the egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff. Sift flour and sugar together.
Mix oil, egg yolks, orange juice and flavoring together;
mix with flour/sugar.
Pour this over egg whites, folding gently with a rubber spatula just until blended. Do not stir.
Bake in ungreased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour; increase to 350° for an additional 10 minutes.
Cool upside down. Run knife around pan to remove.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and cool.
Mix butter, mayonnaise, parsley, garlic, curry powder, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Mix chicken, grapes and almonds in large bowl and place on lettuce leaves.
Put sauce on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: coconut shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving tails on; devein shrimp and rinse in water with lime juice of one lime and drain well.
Combine dry ingredients and stir to mix.
Beat egg whites until just beginning to form soft peaks.
Do not over beat because they will not stick to the shrimp.
Coat the shrimp well with the flour mixture.
Dip in the egg whites, coating well, then in the coconut.
Heat oil to 375 degrees and deep fry shrimp just until golden.
Serve with Brian's Red Sauce, as a main dish or appetizer.

title: cream of peanut butter soup from the king's arms tavern
directions: In Dutch oven or stock pot, saute onion and celery in butter until soft, but not brown (about 8 minutes).
Stir in flour and stir until well blended.
Add chicken broth and stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and puree mixture, a little at a time, in a blender.
Blend 1 cup soup mix with peanut butter until smooth.
Add this and cream to mixture. Return to Dutch oven and heat over low heat just until hot.
Do not boil.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, butter and milk for 3 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add the vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal; stir well. (Add nuts if used.)
Drop onto wax paper.
Let sit for 3 hours, until ready to eat.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put a layer of sliced potatoes on the bottom.
Salt and pepper.
Add a layer of sliced tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Then add a layer of sliced yellow squash, salt and pepper.
Add a layer of sliced zucchini, salt and pepper.
Add sliced onion and bell peppers, if desired.
Cover with foil.
Cook at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Then brown 2 pounds No Sage Owens Country sausage.
Spread browned sausage on top of vegetables. Then spread low-fat grated Cheddar cheese on top of all.
Cover with foil.
Cook for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter.
Put on high heat.
Time 8 minutes after it comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat promptly.
Hand mix in peanut butter and marshmallow until mixed thoroughly.
Put in cake pan and cool.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Mix and refrigerate for ready use.

title: pralines
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and confectioners sugar.
Let cool to 220°. Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Drop on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Spread torn tortillas in bottom of greased baking dish. Mix cooked chicken, soups and broth, chilies, and onions. Stir in 1 c. cheese. Pour into baking dish and top with rest of cheese. Bake at 350° until mixture is heated through and cheese has melted. Garnish with dollops of sour cream.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple and cherry pie filling in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread out.
Spread dry cake mix on top.
Slice butter and put on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meat balls in mushroom sauce
directions: Mix meat, eggs, cheese and seasonings.
Shape into about 30 (1 1/2-inch) balls; brown slowly on all sides in a little hot fat, about 20 minutes.
Drain off excess fat; pour in soup.
Add 2/3 cup water slowly, stirring to blend.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen sweet dill pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onions, salt and water in plastic bowl.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain, don't rinse.
Put sugar, dill and vinegar. Let stand until sugar melts.
Pour over pickles and freeze.
Put 1 cup or more in Ziploc freezer bags and freeze.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets; measure juice.
Add water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Bring liquids to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon gelatin, sugar, vinegar and horseradish, stirring until gelatin and sugar are dissolved.
Add beets and turn into a 1-quart mold. Chill until firm.
Serves 6.

title: carrot loaf
directions: Saute the onions in the oil in frying pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in loaf pan and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until loaf pulls from side of pan.

title: pilot's grill cheese spread
directions: Finely chop green pepper, onions and pimento.
Mix together with the remaining ingredients.

title: moist pineapple cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in ungreased cookie sheet at least 1-inch deep for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, melted butter, cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Press into buttered spring form mold.
Cream together cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, eggs, one at a time, 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into pan on top of crust.
Bake at 350 for 30 -35 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Mix sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Pour over cheesecake and bake for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Combine soup, eggs, etc. and mix well.
After adding the broccoli, place it in a casserole with crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Sift flour, measure and sift again with soda.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crispy onion rings
directions: Sift flour, corn meal, salt and baking powder.
Add oil, eggs and milk, mixing thoroughly.
Dip onion rings into batter.
Fry in hot deep fat (vegetable oil) for 2 or 3 minutes each side until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel and salt.
Batter good for fish fillets.

title: hard candy
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredient sin a large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310° or until drops of syrup form hard, brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat.
After boiling has ceased, stir in flavoring and coloring.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.
Dust with powdered sugar. Store in airtight containers.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: sausage and shrimp medley
directions: Saute thinly diced sausage and vegetables for 5 to 10 minutes. Add stewed tomatoes, salt, pepper, Lea & Perrins and Tabasco to taste.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Microwave frozen okra on High for 15 minutes.
Add to tomato and sausage mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes. Add raw shrimp and simmer for about 15 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: blueberry tea cake
directions: Stir the shortening to soften.
Add flour, which has been sifted with baking powder, salt and sugar; mix well.
Add milk; beat on high 2 minutes.
Add egg; beat 1 minute.
Stir in blueberries carefully.
Pour into a greased cake pan and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: lemon pudding frosting
directions: Cook lemon pudding, egg yolk and water until thick and clear. Cool.
Add sugar and Crisco.
Beat well, about 3 minutes.

title: cheese ring with strawberry jam
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Sprinkle pecans in an oiled ring mold.
Press cheese mixture on top of nuts.
Chill until firm.
Serve with strawberry preserves in center of cheese ring.
Tastes best on wheat crackers.
Yields one 10-inch ring.

title: gooey cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix cake mix, melted butter and chopped pecans. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple-raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat a 12-cup muffin tin with nonstick vegetable cooking spray.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Make well in center.
Stir together buttermilk, applesauce, egg whites and canola oil in a small bowl.
Pour buttermilk mixture into well of dry ingredients.
Stir just until evenly moistened.
Do not overmix.
Gently fold in apple and raisins.
Divide batter evenly. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: yummy lemon cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well. Add dry ingredients and mix while adding 1/2 of the thawed lemonade.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Should be lightly brown on edges.
Using a pastry brush, brush with remaining lemonade and sprinkle with sugar while hot.

title: southwest roll-ups
directions: Place the first seven ingredients and 1/2 cup cheese in a food processor; blend until smooth.
Spread evenly over tortillas. Roll up and place seam side down in a greased 9x13 baking dish.

title: patchwork casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Spoon 1/2 the mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with half of cheese.
Top with remaining meat and potato mixture.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover.
Cut remaining cheese in decorative shapes.
Arrange in patchwork design on casserole.
Let stand for 5 minutes or until cheese shapes have melted.
Serves 6.
Can be frozen.
tags: frozen southern style hash brown potatoes

title: summer squash and zucchini casserole
directions: Dice summer and zucchini squash. Chop onion. Beat eggs and milk together. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Mix well. Pour into a 9-inch square or 11 x 7-inch greased baking dish. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes until liquid is absorbed and contents are golden. Serves 8 as a side dish.

title: baked chicken
directions: In a baking pan, place chopped onions with peels, garlic with peels, tomatoes, celery, carrots and water.
Salt and pepper chicken; place on top of ingredients in baking pan and bake for 45 to 60 minutes in 375° oven.
After 20 minutes, baste with beer. Baste every 1/2 hour.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and next three ingredients together; add to creamed mixture. Add remaining ingredients and stir lightly just enough to mix. Spoon drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: food processor french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine flour and salt in processor bowl and mix for a few seconds.
Add dissolved yeast. With machine running, slowly pour in approximately 1 cup water.
A soft ball of dough should form in a few seconds.
If dough is too sticky, add flour a tablespoon at a time.
If dough is too dry and ball does not form, add water a teaspoon or so at a time.
Process about 1 minute after ball forms to knead dough.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through. Put potatoes in a baking dish and sprinkle salt over them. Drizzle with butter. Sprinkle with herbs. Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes. Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese. Bake potatoes for another 10 minutes, until lightly browned, the cheese is melted and the potatoes are tender inside.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In large frypan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add mushrooms, green pepper and garlic.
Saute 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt (1 teaspoon) and pepper.
Slowly add warm cream and chicken broth (1 1/2 cups).
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Reduce heat to low and add wine.
To beaten egg yolks add a little of the wine sauce then add to mixture in pan.
Add chicken pieces, stirring until heated.
Cook spaghetti in remaining broth and water.
Add remaining salt and bay leaf to broth.
Arrange in greased shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Spoon sauce over spaghetti and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with olives.

title: maids of honor
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl.
Mix in lard or shortening, then, using a knife to cut and stir, mix with cold water to form a stiff paste.
Turn dough on a floured board or work top and roll out. Cut in rounds, using a 3-inch cutter; line 16 to 18 pastry tins. Place a little jam in each pastry.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, cheese, parsley flakes and salt until well blended. Coat chicken with that mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: punch base
directions: Take a sterilized jar or bottle and fill to the neck with clean crystalized sugar (fine white crystals).

Then take the juice of limes (lemons) freshly extracted and putting a glass funnel with a clean muslin cloth, filter this juice into the bottle, shaking the bottle to allow the juice to saturate the sugar (cork it tightly before shaking).
It will take the juice of nearly 2 pounds limes.
Cork it and place it in bright sunlight daily for 6 hours for 3 days.
This will keep for 3 months.

title: crab puffs
directions: Thaw avocado dip according to directions.
In a saucepan, combine water, salt, butter and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to full rolling boil on high heat.
Add flour all at once.
Remove from heat and stir vigorously until mixture is smooth and leaves the sides of pan.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition or until dough is smooth and satiny.
Stir in chives and crab.
Heat deep fat to 375°.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook, turning occasionally, until golden on all sides, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve with avocado dip.
Makes 3 dozen appetizers.

title: chicken-cheese crepes
directions: Cheese Sauce:
Melt butter; stir in flour and salt.
Add milk, water and chicken granules all at once.
Cook and stir on medium heat until thick and bubbling.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in cheese, parsley and pepper sauce (to taste).
Remove 1 cup of sauce mix; set aside.
Stir mushrooms into sauce.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except the potatoes together.
Fold in potatoes.
Place mixture in a greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove the foil the last 10 to 15 minutes for browning.

title: ritz cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter between Ritz crackers and set aside.
In a double boiler or in the microwave, melt the almond bark and chocolate chips in a small bowl.
With tongs, dip Ritz crackers in chocolate/almond bark mix and lay on wax paper to cool.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add rest of ingredients. Mix until well blended. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil margarine, cocoa, milk and sugar together for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter or chocolate chips and coconut (if desired).
Stir well.
Place cookies on either waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Chill.
Makes about 18 large cookies.

title: ham and noodles
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: In large baking pan, break biscuits and cornbread into small bits.
Add baking powder and poultry seasoning.
Simmer celery and onion in chicken broth for 30 minutes.
Add to dry ingredients. Add cooked sausage to mixture.
Using mixture of 1/2 turkey broth and 1/2 water, add to mixture until moist consistency.
Add salt and pepper.
Taste and add seasonings, as needed.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: no bake orange slice cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Keep in a cool place.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook roast and all ingredients in a large covered pan on 300° for 3 hours.
Take out and shred with 2 forks.
Bake, uncovered, 3 hours longer.
Stir frequently.

title: limesea twist
directions: In large pitcher, combine Crystal Light and water.
Mix in water and pineapple juice.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Chill and serve.
Makes approximately 20 servings (4 ounces each).

title: sour cream marinated chicken breast
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; blend well and coat breasts with marinade.
Put breasts in 9 x 13 baking dish; cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 12 hours.
Remove from dish and coat with Italian bread crumbs (crushed Cheez-Its are great).
Put breasts in a clean 9 x 13 lightly greased glass dish.
Pour 1/4 cup melted butter over the coated bread crumb breasts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour another 1/4 cup melted butter over breasts and bake 15 minutes more.
Total baking time is 1 hour. Serves 10.

title: quick 'n simple southwestern chili
directions: In 6-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, cook onion and peppers in oil until tender.
Add meat; cook and crumble until no longer pink. Drain. Add remaining ingredients and blend well. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Yield: 10 cups.

title: rose geranium cake
directions: One day prior to baking, wrap 6 or 7 Rose Geranium leaves around each stick of shortening (see also icing recipe for day-before instructions).

title: candied sweet potato
directions: Drain potatoes and slice.
Arrange in a casserole dish.
In small saucepan, melt margarine and brown sugar together until smooth.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
When almost done, top with marshmallows if you like.
This is optional.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat together.
Spread in pan.
Top with El Paso taco sauce, 8 ounces Cheddar cheese and shredded lettuce.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Lay chicken breasts smooth side down between two sheets of waxed paper.
Pound each breast to the thickness of between 1/8 to 1/4-inch (use meat mallet or rolling pin).
Mend any tears in meat. Sprinkle breasts lightly with salt and pepper.
Keeping smooth side down, place a piece of ham and cheese on half of the breast.
Trim if it overlaps.
Fold the other half over and pinch and pound the edge together to seal.
Dip lightly in flour, then eggs, then bread crumbs.
Place them on waxed paper on a plate and refrigerate for at least an hour to give crust drying time.
Saute chicken in oil and margarine, turning frequently for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: butter rum balls
directions: Note:
For more of a cookie, use 1 1/2 cups nuts.
Cream butter; add sugar, flavor, flour, then nuts.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet or until delicate yellow color.
Roll in powdered sugar if desired.

title: acini dipepe salad
directions: Combine sugar, egg, flour, salt and pineapple juice in a saucepan. Cook until thickened. Let cool. Cook acini dipepe. Rinse and drain. Combine cooled
sauce mixture with fruit and cooled acini dipepe. Chill. Add cool whip and mix.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato juice, cumin, garlic salt, salt, pepper and rice.
Mix well. Bring to boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Beat together peanut butter and margarine.
Stir in sugar. Stir in Rice Krispies by hand.
By tablespoon, shape into logs. Roll in nuts.
Set aside.
Melt chocolate and shortening over low heat stirring constantly.
Drizzle over logs.
Chill.
Makes 40 logs.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Prepare enough pie crust for 12 dumplings.
Usually Never Fail Pie Crust will make two or three dumplings, depending on the size of the apple.
Peel and core an apple, taking care to get all the hulls from around the seed area and keep apple intact.
Roll out circle of pie dough and place apple in center.
In center of apple where core was, put generous chunk of butter and one tablespoon brown sugar.
Over all this, put tablespoon or more white sugar. Then sprinkle generously with cinnamon.
Fold dough securely together over the top.
Place in rows in baking dish.
Baste at the first with apple dumpling sauce and then about every 10 minutes during the baking.
Bake at 350° until fork inserted in top of dumpling shows that the apple is tender.
Time and amounts of this recipe depend largely on the size and kind of apple.
We like to use Winesap because of the tartness but Washington is good, too.
Be sure to use all the sauce on the dumplings.
Serve warm with ice cream or a slice of cheese on top.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fruit apple dip
directions: Mix together until well blended and smooth.
Good for tart apples.

title: fried onions and potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in large frying pan with small amount of shortening.
Sprinkle onion onto potatoes.
Add salt.
Bring to a good fry on high heat.
Pour water into potatoes after they begin to brown.
Cover and cook until tender.
Great with pinto beans!

title: hazel's christmas cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients together and chill overnight.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters (not too thin!).
Bake until lightly browned in a 350 oven.
Cool.
Frost with confectioners sugar frosting and sprinkle with colored sugar, etc to decorate.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Set oven to 350° to preheat.
Grease 3 empty No. 2 or 303 size cans or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Chop nuts.
Mash bananas.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Combine butter, sugar, egg and flavoring in mixing bowl.
Cream on Beat-Whip speed for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stop; scrape bowl and add bananas, cream, nuts and flour mixture.
Beat on Stir-Mix speed about 1/2 minute or until well blended.
Fill cans about 2/3 full.
Bake 1 hour or until done. Loosen and remove from cans.
Cool thoroughly before serving. Makes about 30 (1/8-inch) slices per can.

title: strawberry spinach salad
directions: Mix the strawberries, spinach, drained oranges and chopped cashews in large salad bowl.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, eggs, butter and oil.
Add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.
Shape into balls.
Dip balls in white sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until edges are golden.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Make jello as usual, using pineapple juice as part of your cold water.
(Use water as for large jello only.)
Add other ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Unmold.

title: applesauce sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes or yams and place chunks in large baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt.
Put applesauce on the pieces and sprinkle lightly with cinnamon. Mix brown sugar, oatmeal and melted butter and sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Save a little melted butter and applesauce for bottom of pan.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Beat eggs; mix sugar, milk and vanilla.
Mix with crumbled biscuits.
Bake in 350° oven until thick.
You can make rice pudding with this.
Use 2 cups rice instead of biscuits.

title: popeye muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, oil and eggs.
Stir until combined.
Stir in spinach and 1 1/4 cups of the cheese.
Evenly spoon batter into cupcake papers.
Sprinkle muffins with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until toothpick comes out clean and cheese is melted.

title: macaroni cloud in a mug
directions: Stir milk into cornstarch.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Reduce heat to low.
Add cheese and corn.
Stir to melt cheese.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks lightly.
Slowly add cheese mix.
Stir constantly.
Fold in macaroni; cool slightly. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold into macaroni mix.
Fill four 12-ounce ovenproof mugs or 10-ounce custard cups with mix.
Leave 1/4 inch at top.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed.
Add creamed corn; mix well and put in a casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs and bake 12 minutes (about 350°).

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add onions and pepper and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, ketchup, rice, and water.
Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes until rice is done.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil and peel potatoes.
Slice into 1/8-inch thickness or thinner; set aside.

title: corn bread fritters
directions: Mix flour and meal thoroughly. Add buttermilk until the mixture is thin enough to pour, like pancake batter.
Put 1 tablespoon of the bacon grease in an iron skillet.
Heat until hot.
Pour in 1/4 cup batter. Brown on both sides.
You can fry about 4 or 5 at the same time in a 10-inch skillet. Add a tablespoon of bacon grease as needed.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: In ungreased square pan, stir together first 9 ingredients. Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Spoon into dish and top with ice cream.
Spoon sauce over each serving.

title: elaine's ham and cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven on 375°. Cook for 45 minutes. Toss together cheese, ham, and onion. Spoon into pie shell. Whisk the rest of the ingredients until blended up good. Pour over ham and cheese mixture.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 of the French fried onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: flavorful rice
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion and mushrooms and saute over medium heat until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add rice and brown quickly.
Stir in spices and raisins.
Pour water over rice, cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Add pine nuts and serve.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Add raisins to 1 cup water and boil 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Add ingredients.
Drop batter by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to boil the first 4 ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Then add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir quickly and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: peach pie
directions: Dissolve
jello
in
boiling water.
Beat in ice cream. Add peaches and whipped topping.
Put into baked pie shell.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in electric blender. Mix until completely blended, 5 to 8 minutes. Refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first five ingredients plus 1/2 cup of catsup.
Place in loaf pan.
Mix remainder of ingredients and pour over top.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, eggs, onion, bell pepper, parsley, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
When mixed, roll it out into the form of a loaf and place it in a 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Place the 2 slices of bacon over the meat loaf and cover with tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Heat sugar, chocolate and evaporated milk until chocolate melts and ingredients come to a boil.
Cook on high for 15 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add margarine, Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and nuts.
Beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Pour into buttered greased pan.
Cut when warm for best results.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Add enough water to nectar to make 2 cups.
Heat and dissolve Jell-O in liquid.
Drain cherries and cut in half.
Add cherries, pineapple and nuts to Jell-O mixture.
Stir well and refrigerate until set.

title: cornflake chicken
directions: Combine cornflakes, dressing and Parmesan cheese in bowl.
Dip chicken in milk; roll in crumb mixture.
Place chicken in lightly greased dish.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: crock-pot chili beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 8 hours.

title: sour cream chocolate drops
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add corn flakes.
Set aside.
In top of double boiler, over hot water, melt 2 squares of chocolate.
In a large bowl, beat shortening, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes at medium speed.
At low speed, beat in sour cream, vanilla and flour mixture, then chocolate; beat just until combined.
Chill dough 1 hour.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Refrigerate for 1 hour. Remove and shape into balls, using about 1/8 cup of mixture for each ball.

title: tuna or salmon loaf(can be made into cakes.)
directions: Combine all ingredients except oleo.
Use oleo to grease loaf pan or melt into skillet.
If making loaf, pat mixture into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until loaf is firm and done, or shape mixture into 6 patties and add patties to melted oleo and "fry" cook in skillet until brown and crispy. Turn patties and brown.
Serve hot!

title: taco dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine this with sour cream, Miracle Whip and taco seasoning.
Layer as follows (on serving platter):
bean dip, avocado mixture, sour cream, onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheesy chowder
directions: Combine bouillon cube, water and potatoes in large pot and cook 10 minutes.
Add onion and assorted veggies.
Cook 10 minutes or until done.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly until Cheez Whiz is melted; do not boil.
If soup is thin, add 2 tablespoons cornstarch, mixed with 1/4 cup cold water.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Seperate the rolls into triangles Place link on wide end of each triangle and roll up. Place tip down on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 400° for 10-15 min. or until golden brown. Yield 8 servings

title: butterscotch noodles(candy)
directions: Melt chips.
Stir in nuts.
Stir in noodles.
Using a teaspoon, drop onto waxed paper and allow to harden.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Do not drain excess water or cook until dry.
Stir sausage and sour cream into the rice and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: velvet crumb cake
directions: Grease and flour a square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch) or round pan (9 x 1 1/2-inch).
Beat all ingredients except topping on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed for 4 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool slightly; spread with topping.
Set oven control to broil.
Broil cake with top 3 inches from heat for about 3 minutes or until topping is golden brown.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs and flour alternately. Add vanilla.
Bake in tube cake pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.
(Due to different ovens, watch closely the last 15 minutes of baking.)

title: very good angel dessert
directions: Slice the cake and put half in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the milk and water until smooth.
Add pudding and fold in Cool Whip. Add vanilla and mix. Smooth half on cake, then half the peaches. Add another layer of cake, the rest of the topping and the remainder of the peaches.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: sauce piquant(pi-caw)
directions: In saucepan melt butter and saute onions.
Cook until onions are lightly browned.
Add Ro-Tel, tomato sauce and tomato paste and approximately 5 cups water. Cook on low until sauce thickens. Add salt, red pepper, garlic and chili powder.
Add meat and approximately 2 cups water.
Cook 30 minutes on low, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: southern style green beans
directions: Lightly fry bacon in saucepan.
Add onion; fry until bacon is crisp.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper; stir well.
Yields 4 servings.

title: canadian honey drops
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in honey and vanilla.
Blend flour and soda.
Stir in.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and melted butter.
Add well beaten eggs and pecans.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and water.
In pan, boil oleo and oil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix by hand, then add the eggs.
Pour in greased 16 x 20-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cover with Chocolate Sheet Cake Icing.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak crumbled biscuits in hot water for a few minutes.
Add sugar, butter, vanilla, milk, beaten eggs and nutmeg, mixing after ingredients are added.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: thick hot chocolate
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Gradually add milk.
Stir until boils real good.

title: impossible ham and swiss pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch). Sprinkle ham, cheese and onion in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients for 1 minute.
Pour into plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, usually 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: party hot dogs
directions: Mix equal parts of mustard and jelly in saucepan; stir until well blended over medium heat.
Slice hot dogs into bite size pieces.
Add to mixture.
Simmer until hot dogs are done.

title: huli-huli spareribs
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in bowl.
Add spareribs and toss to thoroughly coat pieces with sauce.
Reserving sauce, remove ribs and place, meaty side up, in a 9 x 13-inch microwave-safe dish.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cover and microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 16 minutes, rotating dish once.
Place ribs on grill 4 to 5 inches from medium-hot coals.
Brush with reserved sauce.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes; turn and brush occasionally with sauce or place ribs on rack of broiler pan and brush with reserved sauce; broil 4 to 5 inches from heat source 6 minutes on each side.
Brush once with remaining sauce.

title: old-fashioned cabbage rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend meat with egg, milk and bread crumbs. Stir in salt, ginger, nutmeg, allspice and onion.
Mix well.
Cut out core of cabbage.
Carefully separate outer 10 to 12 leaves (reserve remainder for other use).
Remove center thick vein of each leaf.
Drop leaves into boiling water.
Cover.
Steam 3 minutes or until soft and bright green.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Reserve liquid.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into small balls.
Chill balls for an hour.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip balls into melted chocolate.
Let cool.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container and refrigerate.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Heat apple juice on low and add apples as you slice them. Remove with a slotted spoon and place in pie shell.
Add spice and cornstarch to juice and stir well until thickened.
Pour over apples.
Top with remaining crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemon juice.
Cool. Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add gelatin and mix well.
Fold whipped Milnot into gelatin mixture.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes; cut into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few at a time in the bag, coating well with cheese mixture.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Blend cornstarch and sugar; stir in Sprite (carbonated beverage).
Cook and stir until clear, add red food coloring.
Pour over fresh strawberries in already baked pie crusts.
May add Cool Whip or whipped cream to cooled pie.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls according to directions (lay out flat). Mix next 3 ingredients and spread on baked dough.
Top with chopped vegetables of your choice and top with shredded cheese.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix Jiffy corn meal mix as on box, using the three eggs.
Add the rest of the ingredients and bake at 350° until done.
No longer than cornbread takes.

title: butternut kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add the flour, baking soda and salt. Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in ground nuts. Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes or until set. Press Kiss in center of each cookie.
Cool on wire rack.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Drain spinach and artichokes. Mix all ingredients (except Parmesan cheese). Spread in a casserole dish. Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 375° until cheese browns.

title: devil's float
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Mix milk, vanilla and shortening.
Add dry ingredients and nuts; mix well. Put in deep greased 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: sweeter muffins
directions: Grease muffin tins and preheat oven to 350°.
Makes 12 muffins. In mixing bowl, beat egg slightly with a fork.
Stir in milk and oil.
Measure and blend the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add all at once to liquid mixture.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
No extra strokes!
Fill each cup approximately 1/2 full.
Wipe off any spilled batter.
Place in center of oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.
Loosen and lift out. Serve piping hot.

title: cream cheese pecan roll
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Form into a ball and roll in pecans.

title: kitchen sink casserole
directions: Arrange in layers:
potatoes, carrots, corn and rice.
Mix ground beef and onions together with salt and pepper to taste. Put mixture on top of rice.
Pour can of tomatoes over meat. Punch holes in the top so juice goes down.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Grated cheese may be added on top, if desired.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer peas, asparagus, soup and crackers.
After all are layered top completely with cheese. Bake in moderate oven at 350° until bubbly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Add other ingredients.
Chill.

title: deer meat with spicy sauce
directions: Cut tenderloin into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Brown in skillet in 1/2 cup oil.
Sprinkle with Molly McButter and garlic salt. After meat loses red color, add dry mustard and sugar.
Reduce heat and add tomato juice, pepper seed, green pepper and onion. Simmer for about 1 hour, covered.
If necessary, thicken sauce with cornstarch.
Serve over cooked Uncle Ben's long grain rice.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and place into a small casserole dish. Heat in a 325° oven
until mixture is hot and cheese has melted. About 20 to 30 minutes.

title: home style chicken noodle soup
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine broth, carrot, celery, onion, parsley, poultry seasoning and thyme.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: slaw salad
directions: Mix slaw, sunflower seed, almonds, and noodles.

title: wayne's summer pepper dish
directions: Cook peppers and onion with the dressing drizzled over. You want enough liquid to gently simmer. In covered casserole, bake at 375° for 3/4 hour, stirring occasionally. Cook until softened. Spread cheese over peppers. Place under broiler until cheese is melted.

title: fannie mae fudge
directions: Cook sugar and cream on stove.
Boil for 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter, vanilla and chocolate chips, beating with spoon until smooth.
Add nuts and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix together.
Add white vinegar to thin.
This recipe will serve 8 people.

title: barbecued catfish
directions: Mix all sauce ingredients and pour over fish.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Place on grill.
Baste with remaining sauce.

title: greek style pockets
directions: Filling:
In large saucepan, cook meat until no longer pink; drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, allspice, garlic salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring often.
Uncover and simmer 10 minutes more or until most of liquid evaporates, stirring often.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer from bottom, bean dip and dressing first.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning and put as layer.
Third layer is tomatoes, then onions and olives.
Sprinkle top with cheese.

title: chicken-macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
In a medium bowl combine macaroni, flaked chicken and next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
In a small bowl, blend remaining ingredients.
Add to salad mixture; toss to coat.
Cover; chill.
Toss before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: scalloped cattails
directions: Drop the cattails into a quart of boiling water and boil for 4 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Scrape off enough of the green part to make about 1 1/4 cups and place in a bowl.
Add egg, butter, nutmeg and pepper.
Mix well.

title: cherry upside-down crisps
directions: Put cherry pie mix in 9 x 13-inch pan (approximate).
Sprinkle 1 cup of cake mix over the cherries.
Pour 1/2 cup melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° until brown and crispy (15 minutes).

title: honey carrot cake
directions: Beat together and pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's jello salad(childrens recipe)
directions: Mix first three ingredients together with Jello. Mix well. Stir in marshmallows.
Serve in ice cream cones or cups.
Great for grandchildren.

title: berry sauce
directions: Rinse, drain and hull or clean berries.
Should have 2 cups berries.
Puree berries along with remaining ingredients in a blender or a food processor until smooth.
If berries have seeds, strain after pureeing.
Serve with cakes, poached fruits and custards.

title: honey-mustard chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Arrange chicken in single layer in baking dish.
Stir together honey, mustard, soy sauce, salt and ground hot red pepper in small cup.
Brush chicken with half of the honey-mustard mixture.
Place chicken in preheated oven. Immediately reduce oven temperature
from 450° to 375°.
Bake 55 minutes for fryer and 30 to 45 minutes for boneless chicken breasts.
Baste two or three times during cooking.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels with peanut butter in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Stir until blended. Stir in Rice Krispies. Press half of the mixture in buttered 8-inch square pan. Chill, setting remainder aside.
Stir the chocolate morsels, confectioners sugar, butter and water over hot water until chocolate melts.
Spread over the chilled mixture. Top with the other half of Rice Krispies mixture.
Chill. Cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt velveeta, mix all items together.
Warm in the oven to desired heat.

title: fly-off-the-plate rolls
directions: In small bowl, dissolve the yeast and 1/2 teaspoon sugar in the 1 cup warm water and set aside.
In large bowl, mix together hot water, sugar, margarine and salt.
Stir in 6 to 8 cups of flour and then stir in the yeast mixture.
Add rest of the flour to make a soft dough and knead very good.
Let rise.
Knead down and it is ready to put in greased pans.
May make rolls, sweet rolls, tea rings, etc.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.
Family favorite!

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all together and leave in refrigerator all night.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Mix butter and sugar thoroughly.
Stir in flour.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Chill dough.
Roll out 1/3 to 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into fancy shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake (the tops do not brown during baking, nor does the shape of the cookies change) at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen 1 x 1 1/2-inch cookies.

title: latin americans
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients together.
Blend butter and sugar. Mix molasses and coffee.
Add to butter mixture alternately with flour.
Fold in chocolate.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water, add sugar and beat on Mixmaster.
Add salt and half of the flour.
Beat well.
Add egg and oil; beat the rest of the flour in it.
When the consistency of dough, place in a large pan, cover with a damp cloth and place in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: vegetable tree
directions: Spread dough onto pizza or cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions.
Mix cream
cheese
and
mayonnaise
with Hidden Valley dressing.
Spread
on dough.
Chop cauliflower, broccoli and peppers.
Spread vegetables over cream cheese generously.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, then add and beat in condensed milk, one can at a time.
Mix in sugar and add vanilla and whole milk.
This may be varied with fruits; just add them before the whole milk so that you can adjust it to the freezer capacity.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and reserve juice.
Add all other ingredients. You may add some of the juice if needed.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk and lemon juice together. Pour into graham cracker crust. Keep in refrigerator.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut up.
Mix with soup, cheese and curry powder.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain; put in buttered casserole.
Pour chicken mixture over it.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.
Additional grated cheese may be added to top.

title: italian eggplant parmigiana
directions: Cut eggplant crosswise into slices about 1/4 inch thick.
Pat into a colander; sprinkle with salt.
Leave to drain 30 minutes. Wipe dry with paper toweling.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of the oil in a large skillet until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water, basil, oregano, 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Cook slowly, uncovered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. Dust each eggplant slice with flour; dip in beaten eggs.
Fry on both sides in hot oil in another skillet until soft and golden, adding more oil as needed.
Drain on paper toweling.
Line a 2 1/2-quart shallow baking dish with a little of the tomato sauce. Arrange a layer of eggplant slices over it.
Cover with a layer of Mozzarella slices, more sauce and sprinkling of grated cheese. Repeat layers to use all ingredients.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes until eggplant is tender and golden on top. Garnish with fresh, if you wish.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mustard leg of lamb
directions: Trim all fat from lamb; place on baking rack in roasting pan. Spread mustard over entire leg of lamb and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Peel and slice onions.
Cover meat with onions.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: cherry chocolate cake(fast, easy and very moist)
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and cherries.
Mix until well blended. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched. Frost when cool with frosting.

title: glossy chocolate frosting
directions: Combine chocolate and shortening.
Melt over hot water; add sugar and milk.
Blend well.

title: crispy vegetables with orange flavor
directions: Combine tofu and soy sauce in medium bowl; toss to coat.
Set aside.
Combine bouillon mixture and cornstarch in measuring cup; blend well and set aside.
Heat oil in large nonstick skillet or wok over medium-high heat until hot.
Add celery, broccoli, red pepper, green onions, orange peel and ginger; cook and stir 4 minutes, or until mixture is slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Gently stir in reserved tofu; cook about 1 minute more, or until heated through.
Serve over spaghetti.
Garnish with orange slices, if desired.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add crushed vanilla wafers alternately with milk.
Add coconut and pecans.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 275°.
Also works in 13 x 9-inch pan for 1 hour.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and pour in ovenproof casserole dish.
Add rice, uncooked, to butter.
Pour soup, consomme and mushrooms over rice and butter.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven or until rice is tender.

title: lucy's mayonnaise
directions: Stir together; cook until thick.
Stir constantly.
Put some commercial mayonnaise with the homemade mayonnaise and use as a dressing for potato salad.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Begin with roux, then add onions, garlic and celery; cook until soft.
Add broth, tomatoes and spices.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve with 4 to 6 cups of rice.

title: christmas tree wreath cookies
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in double boiler. Add food coloring and cornflakes. Drop one teaspoonful at a time on wax paper. Shape with spoon into round and flat shape.
Decorate with red hots.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cook 10 to 15 minutes at 375° on cookie sheet.
Remove from sheet while hot and let cool.

title: creamy-cheesy chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in casserole dish.
Cover with soup and place 1 slice of cheese on each piece of chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: tandy kake
directions: Mix egg, vanilla and sugar.
Add flour and baking powder. Scald milk and margarine together and add to other mixture.
Pour in petit four pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While hot, spread peanut butter.
Let cool good.
Melt chocolate in double boiler and spread on cold cake.
Enjoy.

title: mama's relish
directions: Mix vinegar and sugar in a cup with salt and pepper to taste. Pour over chopped vegetables.
Rinse cup with about 1 tablespoon of water and add to mixture.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Layer:
1 can creamed corn, 1 can whole kernel corn and cracker crumbs.
Repeat, ending up with crumbs.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
With a knife, twist several holes through layers and fill up holes with milk.
Put pats of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cat's creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl. Slowly beat with beater 1 minute. Chill in baked 9-inch pie shell at least 2 hours.

title: cocoa pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients into a small bowl.
Add flour and milk to egg mixture alternately.
Add vanilla.
Grease and flour large Bundt or tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from pan at once.
Ice while still warm.

title: burritos
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add refried beans, chilies and Ro-Tel.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve in flour tortillas.

title: chocolate pecan turtle squares
directions: In food processor, process flour, 1 cup brown sugar and 8 tablespoons butter until sandy.
Pat dough firmly into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle pecans over dough.

title: jello salad
directions: Boil water; add jello and dissolve.
Add juice.
Refrigerate until jello starts to set.
Add applesauce and stir.

title: milk chocolate fudge
directions: Bring sugar, oleo, milk and cream to a boil quickly, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat when bubbles appear all over.
Stir 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chips.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased pan and cool. Cut into pieces when set.
I make this at Christmas.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs and add to cooled melted butter.
Add sugar, sift flour on the sugar and beat together well.
Add vanilla and buttermilk and stir.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake in moderate oven 50 to 60 minutes until top is lovely brown and a silver knife comes out clean.

title: marinated turkey breast
directions: You will need a large Reynolds oven bag.
Rinse and pat dry turkey.
Place in bag in baking pan.
Pour over vinegar and oil. Then sprinkle spices over turkey.
Close bag and cut 4 small slits in top to vent.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.

title: holly treats
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until mixture is "soft".
Add green coloring, slowly pour in cornflakes, and reduce heat while stirring.
Spoon on wax paper.
Add 3 red hots.
Set and cool.
Makes 12 to 15 treats.

title: cheesy potatoes(excellent for potluck social or recipe can be halved for family.)
directions: Place cooked, diced potatoes in large bowl.
Melt butter.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix sauce through potatoes completely.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 275°.
Flavor improves if made the day before and dish may be frozen.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Combine first 6 items in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix well. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or soft ball stage.
Add pecan halves.
Stir until coated.
Spread on wax paper.
Separate with fork.
Cool.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: creamy fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, over medium heat, melt candy coating and butter with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly onto wax paper-lined 9 or 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Chill 3 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store tightly covered at room temperature or in refrigerator.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: chicken delight
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix chicken broth and mushroom soup.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Pour chicken broth mixture over chicken.
Drain tomatoes; spread tomatoes on top of chicken.
Cover; place in oven and bake 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: caramel corn candy
directions: Combine popped corn and peanuts in a large mixing bowl; set aside.
Combine butter, corn syrup, sugars and salt in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; quickly stir soda and flavorings. Pour over popcorn mixture; mix well.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients together.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill for 2 hours or more. Top with Cool Whip.

title: peanut popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar, molasses, vinegar and butter in saucepan.
Cook, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Continue to cook without stirring until syrup forms a brittle ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, stirring only enough to mix it through the hot syrup.
Have corn and peanuts mixed well in a large bowl. Pour cooked syrup slowly over corn, mixing well.
Wet hands slightly and shape corn into balls.
Makes 12 balls.

title: nut bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over soda.
Stir until dissolved; refrigerate until cool.
In an extremely large bowl, cream shortening and gradually beat in sugar, then eggs.

title: goody bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan/dish (Pyrex), well-greased and floured. Mix second three ingredients and pour over top of other (spread evenly).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let it cool well before cutting into small squares.

title: edna's lime green punch(number of servings: 15 to 20.)
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O and sugar in 4 cups boiling water. Add the remaining 3 cups water, the lemon, pineapple and orange juice. Mix well. Place in container and freeze well.

title: freeze and bake bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, bran, sugar, raisins, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In small mixer bowl, combine eggs, evaporated milk, water and oil.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter into 36 paper-lined muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Place in freezer. When frozen, place in plastic bag and seal.
When ready to use, bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, water and sour cream in casserole dish. Crush crackers and spread on top of mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper together in 1/2 stick of oleo. Take the other 1/2 stick oleo and melt in skillet.
Crush Ritz crackers, put into melted oleo and stir well until oleo is on the crackers.
Mix squash, onions and bell pepper together.
Mix eggs and mayonnaise together, salt, black pepper with mushroom soup and add to squash mixture.
Bake in long baking dish with crackers sprinkled on top.
You can also put grated cheese on top, too.

title: christmas bonbon balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips and paraffin, and refrigerate.
Melt paraffin and add the chocolate chips.
Make balls out of refrigerated mix; stick a toothpick in them and dip in chocolate.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: In a large bowl mix flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add remaining ingredients one at a time.
Mix well with spoon.
Do not beat. Bake in a greased and floured tube or loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Start in a cold oven.

title: sweet lemon spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving pieces.
Place in skillet with water to cover and bring to boil.
Cover skillet and simmer 1 hour.
Pour off water.

title: polly boileau's no-fail pie meringue
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon cornstarch, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Cook until clear.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat egg whites, which are at room temperature, with salt.
When foamy add the cornstarch mixture, a small amount at a time.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons sugar and continue to beat until it looks like 7-minute icing.
