Cover cream filling, making sure all edges are sealed. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: beef tortilla roll-ups
directions: Cook ground meat until brown. Drain fat.
Stir in sour cream and flour. Add seasonings.
Place a thin layer of spaghetti sauce in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon 1/3 cup meat mixture into each tortilla.
Roll tortilla. Place tortilla, seam down, in pan.
Pour rest of sauce over tortillas.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hazel's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla and cook about 1 1/2 hours.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
To this, add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and food coloring to sugar mixture and mix well.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk.
Three or four layers may be made.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except biscuits in casserole dish. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 400°
until mixture is bubbly.
Quarter biscuits and place on top of casserole.
Bake 15 more minutes, or until biscuits are brown.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 more minutes (low heat).
Beat 2 whole eggs with 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Fold eggs in rice.
Mix quickly.

title: stuffed stellas
directions: Carefully cut the Stella D'Oro rounds in halves and set aside. Cream together the cream cheese and container of Cool Whip.
Add the pineapple (drain all but a small amount of juice from pineapple).
Spoon mixture onto 1/2 of Stella rounds and top with the remainding 1/2 of Stella rounds.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: roast opossum in sauerkraut
directions: Cut the opossum into serving size pieces.
Salt and pepper. Place on a rack in a roasting pan.
Add the wine and garlic; roast for about 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
Add the sauerkraut and the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Turn the heat down, cover and simmer for about an hour.
Serve with boiled potatoes.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Slice potatoes.
Lay in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Lay pork chops on top.
Layer until pan is fairly full.
Mix together milk and both cream soups.
Add onion, black pepper, garlic powder, salt, cracker crumbs and cheese to taste.
Pour on top of potatoes and chops (layer liquid with the layers of potatoes and chops). Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until done.

title: busy day cake
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer a few minutes.
Remove cake from oven and pour mixture over top of the hot cake.

title: corncob jelly
directions: Boil corncobs and water for 30 minutes.
Take 3 cups of juice and pectin and then sugar.
Boil 1 minute.

title: diabetic lemon coconut cookies
directions: Mix oleo, egg and next 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add flour and coconut.
Mix thoroughly and drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 19 minutes.
Three cookies equals 1 bread exchange.

title: twice-baked potato
directions: Cut tops of 4 baked potatoes off lengthwise and scoop out potato, leaving a thin shell.
Mash potato with sour cream, onion salt and chives.
Fill skins with potato mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: corn relish
directions: In a medium saucepan, mix together the corn, green bell pepper, onions, sweet pickle relish, celery seed, salt, dry mustard, vinegar and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Transfer the mixture to sterile jars and refrigerate until serving.
Makes 32 servings.

title: dump cake(makes 12 to 16 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump pineapple (with syrup) into pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread evenly over pineapple.
Dump dry cake mix onto cherry mixture.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix and dot with pieces of butter.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes. Serve warm or cold.
Goes well with ice cream.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Alternate sliced apples and mixture in pie crust until apples are heaped in center.
Dot with butter and top with crust.
Slit crust to let steam escape.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins in 1 cup water for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, cooled raisins and nuts. Add dry ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: sauce good for beef or pork roast
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in refrigerator to use on beef or pork roast.

title: chocolate pie dessert
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix well with melted butter and sugar; press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook chocolate pudding as directed. When pudding comes to a full boil, add 2 candy bars to mixture. Stir until melted; pour into pan. Cool. When completely cooled, put Cool Whip on top of pudding mixture. Put grated candy bar on top.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Blend dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Grate rind from orange and add to flour mixture.
In separate bowl, squeeze juice from orange and add shortening.
Add buttermilk to make 3/4 cup of liquid. Beat egg and add to liquid.
Pour over flour.
Add cranberries and nuts and stir until blended.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes and remove from pan.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time alternating with buttermilk.
Add fig preserves, vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in well-greased and floured tube pan.

title: multi grain blueberry muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine wet ingredients.
Fold quickly wet and dry ingredients just until flour is moistened. Gently mix in blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen large muffins.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into a 1 pound loaf pan.
Bake in 325° oven for approximately 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: compuesto salad
directions: Mix refried beans and jalapeno bean dip together in bottom of large bowl.
Sprinkle onions.
Sprinkle avocados with lemon juice and mash.
Spread over previous ingredients.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread over previous ingredients. Sprinkle Monterey jack cheese and Cheddar cheese over.
Top with shredded lettuce.
Serve with favorite chips.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in large mixer bowl until light. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in pumpkin.
Combine flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder, baking soda, salt and pecans in a small bowl. Add to pumpkin mixture.
Mix just until blended. Spoon into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pans. Cool on wire racks.

title: crumble topping
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter.
Sprinkle on top of canned apple pie mix.
May also be used for cobblers or bought pie filling.

title: rich cranberry coffee cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Add eggs one at a time, mixing well.
Combine 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture. Mix remaining flour with cranberries and nuts.
Fold into batter; batter will be very thick.
Spoon into greased 10-inch pan and bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing from pan. Cool on rack.
Dust powdered sugar on each slice before serving.

title: great grandma kissel's "applejack"
directions: Cover bottom of a 2-quart baking dish with apples first, then cover with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix rest of ingredients together. Pour over apples (don't mix with apples).
Bake at 350° until it first starts to brown.
Turn down until done.
Good with milk and nutmeg in a bowl.

title: chicken and chilies
directions: Chopped green chili peppers and black beans turn this chicken skillet dinner into a South of the Border fiesta!
A tossed salad is a perfect accompaniment.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix the rest of ingredients together; pour over mostaccioli mixture. Refrigerate one to two hours.

Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: fig jam
directions: Bring figs to a boil.
Cook down until desired.
Add sugar and add jello.
Bring to a boil.
Put in jars.

title: english toffee candy
directions: Line jelly roll pan with waxed paper. Cook sugar and butter until candy thermometer reaches 300°, about 25 minutes. Quickly spread in pan. Put chocolate chips over top and let sit until melted. Spread chocolate evenly over the mixture.

title: drop donuts
directions: Beat eggs and stir in buttermilk, vanilla and lemon or orange peel.
Combine flour and baking powder, stir into egg mixture. Cover with a cloth and let stand for 1 hour.
Heat deep fryer to 375°.
Drop batter by a tablespoon just a few at a time.
Drain on paper towel.
Drizzle with honey and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Best served while hot.
Makes about 30 donuts.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, sour cream and pimentos in 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Add to top the grated cheese and onion rings.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: chicken noodles
directions: Place all ingredients, except noodles, into a roasting pan. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: lasagne(this is an old italian recipe!)
directions: Note:
Blend cottage cheese in blender with 1 egg, if a smoother texture is desired.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-aid in pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale and 7-up.
Add pineapple sherbet and ice cream last.
Frozen strawberries are optional.

title: pasta with cilantro, peas and smoked salmon
directions: With blender running, drop garlic and chili through feed tube and chop finely.
Add cilantro; chop finely.
Add cream; blend until thick, using on/off turns.
Add lime juice.
Season sauce with salt and pepper.
Cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender, but still firm to bite.
Add fresh peas if using and boil 2 minutes.
Do not cook frozen peas.
Drain pasta and return to same pot.
Mix in sauce and thawed frozen peas, if using.
Add salmon and chives.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, pepper and onions; set aside.
Heat the remaining 5 ingredients almost to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and etc.
Refrigerate.

title: sloppy joe burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into patties and brown.
Combine chili sauce and water; pour over burgers and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Blend together cream cheese and 1 cup of margarine.
Add flour, then chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 4 dozen (1-inch) balls.
In small muffin tins, place ball in each and work around tin.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Cook chicken with seasoned flour.
Brown in a heavy skillet in hot oil.
Pour off excess oil.
Combine last 4 ingredients; pour over chicken.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: rye bread 'n dip
directions: Rinse beef. Pat dry. Blend all ingredients and chill. Cut and cube center out of 1 small round rye bread. Fill rye bread with dip and use cubed bread to dip.
Double recipe for large one.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except liquid and 1/2 cup noodles. Pour liquid on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Top with 1/2 cup noodles and bake 15 minutes more.
May be garnished with red pimento and green pepper rings on top.
Serves 12.

title: fillets of sole florentine
directions: Combine egg yolks, frozen butter, water, lemon juice and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Stir over medium heat with wire whisk until butter melts and sauce is smooth.
Remove from heat before it becomes too thick.
Cool completely.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fluffy cloud biscuits
directions: Sift in dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Combine milk and egg.
Beat.
Add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut out biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 14 minutes.
Very delicious and light.

title: barbecued ham sandwiches for 25
directions: Mix together and simmer ingredients until vegetables are tender.
Add meat and simmer 1/2 hour.
If sauce seems sour to taste, add white sugar as desired.
Quadruple recipe for 100 people; double recipe for 50 people.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of 12 medium muffin cups (2 3/4-inch diameter).
Beat egg, stir in milk and oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients just until flour is moistened.
(Batter should be lumpy.)
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
For blueberry muffins, fold in 1 cup of fresh berries.

title: walnut patties
directions: Toast bread and roll into crumbs. Cook onions until clear in small amount of butter.
Combine all ingredients except mushroom soup.
Form into thin patties; fry slowly in oil for 30 to 40 minutes.
Place patties in 1 large or 2 medium size casseroles. Cover with slightly thinned mushroom soup and heat in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: graduation punch
directions: Combine undiluted concentrated orange juice with 4 cups cold water in punch bowl. Add additional water and ice cubes; stir until melted. Add ginger ale and sherbet. Garnish with orange slices and strawberries.
Yield: 32 servings of 1/2 cup each.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased pan.
Top with extra cheese.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: lite and lean eggnog
directions: In a bowl, let frozen yogurt stand, stirring occasionally until melted, about 15 minutes. Whisk in milk, rum extract and nutmeg. Cover and chill at least 30 minutes. Sprinkle with nutmeg for garnish, if desired. Makes 8 servings.
Ready to serve in 45 to 50 minutes.

title: "special" sugar cookies
directions: Blend first four ingredients well and cut in butter as for pie crust.
Beat together the egg, sugar and vanilla until white and creamy.
Don't underbeat.
Blend flour and egg mixture until well combined.
Chill four hours.

title: hot dog surprise
directions: Fill 8 wiener rolls with mixture and wrap in foil.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: coconut toast with pineapple
directions: In shallow bowl, beat eggs with the cream or milk, sugar and ginger.
In another bowl, combine corn flakes and coconut.
Heat a griddle over medium heat.
Dip each slice of bread first in egg mixture, then in coconut mixture to coat both sides.
Cook on lightly oiled griddle slowly until browned on both sides.
Remove to warm plates and serve immediately with bowls of pineapple, sour cream and brown sugar for topping.
Makes 3 servings of 2 slices each.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Mix all ingredients with cooked squash; reserve 1/3 of dressing mix for topping.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar, beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add bananas.
Put into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
One-half cup of nuts may be added.
Banana bread freezes very well.

title: raspberry pudding
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Boil last 3 ingredients 5 minutes and pour over batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Boil with 1 cup water the raisins, dates and apples.
Use all the water.
Do not drain.
Boil 3 minutes; add oleo, then cool. Add beaten egg whites, sweetener, vanilla, soda and flour.
Add nuts last.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a well Pam sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate in an airtight container to store.

title: dipped peppermint creams
directions: Line 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with foil.
In medium saucepan over low heat, melt vanilla-flavored candy coating and 1/4 cup shortening, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in peppermint candy.
Spread in foil-lined pan.
Let stand at room temperature until firm.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Soften cream cheese, add eggs, vanilla and sugar.
In small cupcake paper holders, put vanilla wafer on bottom (upside down), then spoon a heaping teaspoonful of cheese mixture on top of wafer.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling.
Makes at least 24 servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Add raw vegetables to chicken broth from cooking chicken.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add other vegetables and chicken.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Use less broth for thicker stew or more broth for thinner stew.
Cook for about 30 to 45 minutes.
This is better if cooked one day and eaten the next.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix food coloring and cocoa to form paste.
Add sugar, shortening and eggs.
Cream thoroughly.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix vinegar and soda.
Blend into batter.

title: chicken everyone loves
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: oreo cookie ice cream dessert
directions: Crush Oreos; reserve 1 cup.
Melt butter; mix with Oreos. Press into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer softened ice cream on top of Oreo crust.
Spread hot fudge sauce on ice cream.
Spread Cool Whip on fudge sauce.
Sprinkle reserved Oreos on top of all. Freeze.

title: aunt kathy's stuffed shells
directions: Brown hamburger and garlic.
Drain.
Blend next four ingredients in bowl. Add browned hamburg.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill until set.

title: english toffee
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
In a heavy pan combine butter, vanilla and salt.
Melt over high heat.
Add sugar and stir until it boils and turns golden.
Pour over nuts.
Melt chips or bark; spread over top. Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in the order given in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan. Refrigerate at least 4 hours to blend tastes.
(Will keep well in refrigerator if made a day ahead.)
Serve with nacho chips or unsalted crackers.

title: apple jelly
directions: Cut green apples in 4th or thinner,
about
4 quarts of apples.
Cook apples in water until
well cooked.
Remove from heat; let cool, then strain apples in a
soft cloth or sifter. Boil
juice and sugar until it drops
from
spoon
thick.
Let foam
for
minutes.
Keep
stirring
or it will boil over. Remove from heat.
Pour into clean jars.
Let stand overnight. Then cover.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until very light, then add egg yolks, beaten until thick and lemon-colored.
Beat again.
Mix and sift together the flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Add to the first mixture along with the milk.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and mace, then fold in egg whites (which have been stiffly beaten).
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tropical fruit delight cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into Bundt pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven and allow to cool. Remove from pan and cool in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Stick holes in cake and spread with frosting.

title: vetebrod (swedish coffee bread)
directions: Melt butter in lukewarm milk.
Add salt, raisins, sugar, cardamom seeds and small amount of flour.
Beat until smooth. Dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup warm water with sugar.
Stir yeast mixture into the milk.
Add egg and 7 to 8 cups bread flour, beating until smooth and firm.
Cover with clean towel and let rise in a warm place until double in size (about 2 hours).

title: hot beef
directions: Bake in oven overnight at 250° or until done.
Pull apart, then add 2 cans golden mushroom soup.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Beat sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla in large mixing bowl on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, about 2 minutes.
Beat in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt, alternating with sour cream on low speed.
Prepare filling for tube pan.
Spread 1/3 of the batter (about 2 cups) in pan and sprinkle with 1/3 of the filling; repeat 2 times.
Bake until wooden toothpick inserted near center comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan.
Cool 10 minutes.
Drizzle with Light Brown Glaze if desired.

title: spicy new orleans chicken
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add chicken pieces; brown lightly.
Stir in seasonings and water, bringing to a boil. Cover and simmer for about 1 hour.

title: chicken wings
directions: Separate chicken wings at joints.
Cut off wing tips.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Drain chicken, reserving marinade. Place chicken in baking dish. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, brushing occasionally with marinade.
Turn chicken and bake an additional 30 minutes, occasionally brushing, until done.

title: chicken divine
directions: In a large baking dish, layer Rice-A-Roni, partially cooked broccoli and boneless breast slices.
Spread soup on top. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and add Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix jello and water together well and cool.
Mix cake mix, jello, oil, eggs and extract well.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into 10-inch Bundt pan (well greased).
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix yeast and water together.
Blend in sugar, egg, oil, salt and powdered milk.
Mix in the flour a little at a time.
Cover and let rise in a warm place.
When dough is doubled in size, add a little flour and knead.
Divide dough in half and place in 2 pans.
Sprinkle with butter, cinnamon and sugar.
Let dough rise again.

title: cranberry citrus ring with chicken salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, gelatin and sugar.
Add water.
Stir until all are dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Peel 1 orange; put peeled orange and unpeeled orange through food grinder, using medium blade.
There should be about 1 cup combined orange juice, pulp and rind.
Add orange mixture and cranberry sauce to gelatin. Mix well, breaking up cranberry sauce with edge of spoon.
Add pineapple and its juice and walnuts.
Turn into ring mold; chill until firm.
Turn out on salad greens to serve.
Fill center with your favorite chicken salad, if desired.
Cranberry mixture may also be set in conventional molds and served without the chicken salad as a dinner salad.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in crust. Refrigerate two hours before serving.

title: one dish chicken dinner
directions: In flat baking dish, put rice, water, dry soup and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix thoroughly, put chicken on top.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Watch, can get dry.

title: jerry's favorite roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place roast in roasting pan.
Mix in saucepan mushroom soup and onion soup.
Add 2 soup cans of water. Heat until blended well.
Pour soup mixture over roast.
May add potatoes and carrots.
Cover and bake for 2 to 3 hours, depending on size of roast.
Soak venison roast overnight in vinegar and water; drain and rinse before cooking.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Spread pretzels on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix melted butter with 2 tablespoons sugar and pour over pretzels and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Whip together the cream cheese, Cool Whip and 3/4 cup sugar.
Spread over cooled pretzels. Dissolve strawberry jello with 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 cup strawberry juice and the sliced strawberries.
When cool and starting to jell, pour over the cream cheese layer and let set until firm.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix beans and onion or pepper if desired.
Boil salt, pepper, sugar, oil and vinegar to boiling.
Pour over beans and refrigerate overnight.
Best with lots of onions.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add the flour slowly; then add the flavorings.
Add 7-Up slowly to the mixture.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan or into two loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
This cake freezes well.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and grated rind or lemon extract. Gradually stir into Eagle Brand milk.
Add egg yolks and stir until well blended.
Pour into chilled crumb crust.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat until almost stiff enough to hold peak.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff, but not dry.
Pile lightly on pie filling.
Bake in slow oven (325°) until lightly brown (about 15 minutes).

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over 2 to 3 pounds of chicken wings.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: shrimp or crawfish fettucini
directions: Melt butter; add onions and bell pepper and cook until tender. Add flour and cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir constantly so not to stick.
Add crawfish and parsley.
Cover and cook 15 minutes. Keep stirring often.
Add half and half, cheese and garlic. Season; cover and cook over low heat about 30 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: bologna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange potatoes, bologna, green pepper, flour and seasonings in layers in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Dot each layer with butter.
Pour milk over all and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mexican casserole a la battle
directions: Brown beef; add taco mix and about 1/3 cup water, plus 4 ounces tomato sauce. Simmer.
Combine 4 ounces of tomato sauce with refried beans, stir and heat.
Crush 1/3 to 1/2 package chips and layer in bottom of casserole dish; top with beef.
Spread beans evenly on top of beef mixture.
Crush remaining chips; combine with cheese and sprinkle on top of beans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: fried eggplant strips
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into finger-size strips. Sprinkle with 1 tsp. salt; cover with water, and soak 1 hour. Drain & pat dry with absorbent towels.

title: three cheese enchiladas
directions: Combine 1/2 of the Monterey Jack with all of the Cheddar and cream cheese.
Add 1/4 cup of sauce.
Add onions and cumin.
Mix well.
Spoon 1/4 cup on a shell and roll.
Place seam side down in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with sauce and remaining Monterey Jack and green onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and lettuce.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper, mushrooms and parsley flakes. Cook 10 minutes.
Add soup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toss peaches with 1 tablespoon of the flour and place in a 6 x 11-inch baking pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over peaches.

title: spicy texas beef stew(contains 435 calories)
directions: Heat the oil in a
heavy
2 quart saucepan over moderate heat for about 1
minute.
Add
the beef, onion and garlic, and cook, uncovered, stirring
frequently, until
the onion is soft and the beef
brown.
Add
tomatoes,
sugar,
cinnamon, cloves, cumin, salt and raisins.
Cover; reduce the heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring
occasionally.
Add
2 or 3 tablespoons of water if the mixture gets too thick.
Serve with rice.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine flour, sugar and salt. Add yeast mixture and stir until well blended.
Turn onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes). Using kitchen shears dipped in flour, cut dough into 18 pieces. Roll each into a ball.
With floured hands, roll each ball into a rope 14 to 16 inches long and 1/2-inch in diameter.
Twist each into a pretzel shape.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Beat egg white until frothy.
Brush on each pretzel.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix rice and beef consomme into a 2-quart casserole dish. Brown pork chops in 1/4 cup grease and place on top of rice.
Cut onion and tomato; place on top of pork chops.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: ukrainian honey bread
directions: *Place a tea bag into 1/2 cup of boiled water.
When the tea turns dark in color, remove the tea bag and let cool.
You want the tea to be strong.

title: mousse
directions: Beat ingredients 4 minutes on high speed.
Spoon into dessert glasses.
Chill.

title: waffles
directions: Sift together in large mixing bowl flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add milk and vanilla to beaten eggs, then add mixture to dry ingredients.
Mix 1 1/2 minutes, until blended.
Add melted butter.
Bake in hot waffle iron.
Serve with chicken and broth. Makes 4 waffles.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all the beans.
Add chopped green pepper, onions, celery and tomato.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Serve on lettuce.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break up fresh crab meat.
Add bread crumbs, salt, pepper, red pepper, parsley flakes and green pepper.
Prepare a white sauce, using milk, flour, mustard and margarine.
Cook until thick.
Add to crab mixture.
Make patties, roll them in cracker meal or bread crumbs.
Fry in lightly oiled or buttered pan.
(May also be broiled with a dot of butter on each crab cake.)

title: birthday punch
directions: Add water to make a gallon.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts; pull off bone and cut in chunks.
Lay in casserole bowl.
Mix and heat mushroom soup, celery soup and sour cream.
Add oleo to soup mixture.
Pour soup over chicken.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and cook 20 minutes or until brown.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: In 2-quart casserole, pour one cup rice, pour in can of mushroom soup, fill empty soup can with water and pour on top of soup.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Soften the shortening.
Gradually beat in the sugar until the mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well. Mix flour, baking powder, salt and spices together.
Stir the dry ingredients into the pumpkin mixture.
Mix until well blended. Add raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cut or tear chicken into pieces. Place in bottom of baking dish.
Mix evaporated milk and soup together and pour over chicken.
Mix the stuffing, butter and broth together.
Pour over top of other ingredients.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: cucumber salad(agurksalat)
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Put in a bowl and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand a couple of hours.
Dissolve sugar in 2 tablespoons water. Mix with oil, vinegar and a little dry mustard.
Pour over cucumbers.
Mix and chill.
Chop parsley and sprinkle over salad before serving.

title: mushroom gravy
directions: Saut mushrooms in 1/2 cup oil in a 4-quart heavy pot.
Drain, reserving oil, and mix mushrooms with 2 quarts broth, onion and garlic.
Blend in blender until smooth.

Mix flour with remaining oil and brown in a heavy pot over medium heat, stirring constantly. While whisking briefly, pour in broth slowly to avoid lumping. Cook over medium-high heat, whisking constantly, until thickened. Ladle enough gravy over potatoes or dish of your choice to coat and place under broiler for 5 minutes or until a browned "skin" forms. It is now ready to display as a centerpiece.
Ladle some gravy over each potato or dish of your choice before serving.

title: monte cristo sandwich
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Mix together the first 6 ingredients and divide among the ten sandwiches.
Lay each sandwich on a square of foil large enough to wrap individually. Wrap tightly and freeze.
Must be frozen.
When ready to use, make a mixture of eggs and milk.
Dip each sandwich with egg mixture and then in crushed potato chips.
Bake on cookie sheet 45 minutes at 300°.
Great for a luncheon with fruit salad.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, confectioners sugar, vanilla, coconut, butter and nuts.
Shape into balls.
Chill for 2 hours or overnight.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Dip balls in mixture and place on foil.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fresh zucchini bread
directions: Blend together sugar, eggs, oil and zucchini.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder, salt, milk and vanilla and blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and pour mixture into 2 greased and floured regular size loaf pans and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Place water and chocolate in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat, stir in sugar and salt. Return to medium heat and cook about 8 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Beat in margarine and vanilla.
Serve hot over ice cream.

title: california "blonde" stew
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut turkey into 1/2 x 1/2-inch slices. Heat oil in 5-quart pot (suitable for baking) over medium heat until oil is hot, about 1 minute.
Place turkey, potatoes, carrots, onion and garlic in pan.
Cook and stir frequently until turkey is no longer pink, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over turkey mixture.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken broth, wine, thyme and pepper and bring to a boil.
Add mushrooms.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Stir in parsley.
Serves 4.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl. Set aside. Beat cake mix, applesauce and eggs in a large bowl until just combined. Reserve 1 1/2 cups batter and set aside. Pour remaining batter into greased 10-inch fluted tube pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar mixture; top with reserved batter. Bake cake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool cake in pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes. Remove cake from pan. Cool thoroughly. Sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar, if desired, before serving. Makes 15 servings.

title: english monkey
directions: Add cheese to butter when melted.
To the crumb mixture, add the egg and seasonings.
Blend all together until smooth.
Serve on crackers or toast.

title: colorful peas
directions: Melt oleo.
Add onions and oregano.
Saute one minute.
Add pimiento and olives.
Stir in peas and heat thoroughly over low heat.
Adjust seasoning.

title: blonde fudge
directions: Cook in a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat; bring to a boil. Cook to a soft ball stage.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Cool.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Beat until it loses its gloss.
Pour into pan.
Cut in blocks.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Make a syrup with the sugar, vinegar and cinnamon.
Cook together for 20 minutes.
Rub skin off peaches by dipping in boiling water.
Rub with cloth.
Stick 2 cloves in each peach. Cook in syrup until peaches are tender.
Put peaches in jar and boil syrup 10 minutes after peaches have been removed.
Pour syrup over peaches and seal.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet and saute onion and bell pepper.
Add all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese in a baking dish, then sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: snicker's ice cream
directions: Melt Snickers in microwave oven.
Blend all other ingredients in melted Snickers bars.
Pour into ice cream freezer and fill to full line with whole milk.
Churn in ice cream freezer.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Easy hot cocoa mix for those cold days!
Mix ingredients in a bucket; will fill a gallon jar.
Mix 1/3 cup of mix with boiling water.

title: beef and cheese manicotti
directions: Boil noodles as directed on package.
Drain, rinse and set aside.
Brown hamburger and drain.
In separate bowl, mix together Ricotta and cottage cheeses.
Add a dash of salt and pepper.
Mix hamburger into the cheese.
Stir together.
Stuff the noodles with the mixture.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Put one can of asparagus in bottom of baking dish.
Add 1/2 can
of
peas.
Pour
can
of
undiluted
celery soup. Sprinkle half of cracker crumbs over top and dot with butter. Repeat layers.
Also
eggs
and grated cheese may be added to top.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mother's chocolate pie
directions: Mix well sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add water.
Cook until it begins to thicken.
Beat egg yolks; add enough syrup to color mixture.
Add egg mixture to chocolate mixture, then add butter. Cook until thick.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; cover with meringue.

title: water chestnut casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Mix all ingredients together, except corn flakes.
Pour in prepared casserole dish.
Crumble corn flakes and sprinkle on top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° until bubbling and golden brown.

title: my favorite pound cake
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar.
Add	eggs,
one
at	a time, beating
well
after each.	Add flour gradually, then vanilla. Bake in a small tube pan for 1 hour at 375°.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: First make a roux with flour and oil.
Add vegetables and simmer, stirring constantly.
Add warm water slowly with remainder of seasonings.
Cook on low heat for 1/2 hour.
Add shrimp. Fifteen minutes later, add oysters and crabmeat and cook for another 15 minutes.

title: dave's chili
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic powder until beef is light brown and onion is tender; drain.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, cumin, salt, sugar, pepper, tomato juice and red pepper sauce, if desired.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beans.
Heat to boiling.
For thicker chili add Masa flour or cornstarch and stir well.
Reduce heat; simmer for an additional 15 minutes.
Serve with shredded Cheddar or Colby Jack cheese.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain and coarsely chop artichoke hearts with food chopper.
Mix artichoke hearts with remaining ingredients in batter bowl.
Then spoon mixture into a mini-baker (9-inch baking dish).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through or when bubbling.
Serve with thinly sliced baguette bread, vegetables and/or crackers.

title: crab burger
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Add pepper.
Cook slowly and set aside to cool.
Place meat in a bowl; remove all particles of shell.
Add salt and pepper.

title: peach bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda and sugar.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in peaches, vanilla, almond extract and nuts.
Spoon batter into greased 9-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: black magic cake
directions: *You can use 1 cup milk that has been curdled with 2 teaspoons of vinegar or lemon juice and allowed to stand about 5 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mash the sweet potatoes and fold in the rest of ingredients. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
One may add 1/4 cup brown sugar and nutmeg for seasoning also.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and cook same as cornbread.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook pasta until done; drain.
Put pasta in a bowl. Add cucumbers, tomatoes and red onion.
Add the whole bottle McCormick Salad Supreme, Parmesan cheese and whole bottle of Italian dressing.
Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: lime-raspberry pie
directions: Reserve a few raspberries for garnish.
In a medium bowl, combine milk and juice.
Fold in topping and raspberries.
Spoon into pie crust.
Cover and chill 3 hours.
Garnish.
Makes 10 servings.
This is very rich, but good!

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan. Arrange pineapple slices on brown sugar.
Place maraschino cherry halves in center of pineapple slices.
Prepare cake mix following package directions for basic recipe.
Pour batter evenly over fruit in pan. Bake at 350° for 43 to 48 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes in pan.
Invert onto serving platter.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: In Dutch oven, saute onion and green pepper strips in butter for 3 minutes.
Add ground chuck and brown, breaking it up with a fork as it cooks.
Add seasoned salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Heat mixture to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cheese.
Whip with milk.
Stir in lemon juice and Worcestershire.
Add garlic to taste.
Salt and pepper.
Add crab shredded.
Chill.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix sugar, pumpkin and eggs together, blending well.
Sift together into mixture flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Grease cookie sheet with oil and line with waxed paper, extending over sides and end of cookie sheet.
Pour batter onto waxed paper and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 375° exactly for 15 minutes, no longer.
While batter is baking, sprinkle clean dish towel (cloth) with powdered sugar.
Flip cooked batter face down on towel.
Remove waxed paper.
Roll loosely.
Roll batter up using dish towel.
Let set until you mix cream cheese, vanilla, butter and powdered sugar. Unroll cake and spread with mixture; roll again.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and in aluminum foil and freeze. Slice while frozen.

title: luann's brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, flour, cocoa and salt. Fold in egg whites and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Ice with fudge icing.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix with rest of ingredients. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sherried beef and onion bake
directions: Blend melted margarine, flour and pepper; add water, sherry and bouillon.
Cook and stir until thick.
Cook 1 minute more.
Remove from heat; stir in stew meat and Kitchen Bouquet.
Place onion wedges in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon meat mixture on top.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 1 3/4 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Bake 30 minutes, in greased and floured pans, either 8-inch round or 9 x 13-inch oblong, until toothpick comes out clean, in a 350° oven.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 - 40 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: baked fresh beef brisket
directions: Mix and put over brisket and bake at 300° for about 4 hours, covered.

title: homemade syrup
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer for 1/2 hour. Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon maple flavoring.
The best syrup ever.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Put in crock-pot and cook several hours or all day.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugar. Beat in vanilla, water and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together and add to sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well. Stir in M&M's.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(You can drop some on top to make faces; orange and brown for Halloween.)

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Squeeze liquid from artichokes.
Drain and dice finely.
Mix all ingredients. Bake in casserole dish for 20 minutes or until brown.
Serve hot in chafing dish with Fritos or Bugles.

title: southwestern potato skins
directions: Pierce Potatoes with a fork; microwave on high for 30 minutes; let cool.
Cut Potatoes in half and scoop out Potatoes leaving 1/4 inch shell.
In medium skillet, brown Beef until crumbly; drain fat.
Stir in Taco Seasonings and Water; bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered 15 minutes.
Stir in Green Onions. Spoon meat mixture into potato shells; top with Tomato, Olives and Cheese.
Place on baking sheet and heat under broiler to melt cheese.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease sheet pan.
Place fruit on bottom.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Cover evenly with melted margarine.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Can use additional sugar, cinnamon and raisins.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain macaroni and set aside.
Cook beef and onion in a large skillet until meat is brown, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain well.
Stir in macaroni, chili beans, enchilada sauce and spices. Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Sprinkle corn chips on top.

title: sangria
directions: Combine wine, brandy, orange juice and lemon juice in a punch bowl; mix well.
Add half of the fruit slices.
Chill for 1 hour. Add remaining fruit slices and club soda.

title: golden crown rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in the lukewarm mixture.
Add eggs.
Add flour; mix to a soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, cover with damp cloth and let rise until double.
Punch down, cover and let rise 10 minutes. Shape into golf size balls.
Roll each in melted margarine and then into sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Arrange in well-greased tube pan; sprinkle with remaining cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes.
Invert on plate and invert again.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar and water on medium heat in saucepan; add peanuts on medium heat.
Stir frequently until syrup cooks out and nuts coated.
Pour on ungreased cookie sheet; stir, breaking apart.
Cook in 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes. Let cool, eat and enjoy.

title: baked flounder with tomato sauce
directions: Grease baking dish.
Arrange fillets in a single layer.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over fish.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: neiman-marcus squares
directions: Mix and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Topping recipe follows.

title: wild rice chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice mix as directed.
Meanwhile, cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, sour cream, wine and curry powder.
Stir in chicken and cooked rice.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish or a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: 1 pot meal
directions: Shape the ground beef in small balls.
Lay in a pot.
Add the vegetables to the meat.
Add water to cover.
Add lid and simmer on top of stove slowly until done.
Much better if made a day before you use it, then you can skim the fat off the top when it is cold.

title: amanda liston's baked beans
directions: Soak beans in hot tap water overnight.
Wash and put into pan with bacon and pork roast.
Add water to cover.
Cook until soft. Add catsup, onions, brown sugar and ham.
Put in casserole and bake at 350°, covered, about 2 hours or until thickened.
Makes a large quantity.
Great for family gatherings.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer 1/2 cake, pudding, strawberries and Cool Whip.
Repeat with other half of ingredients.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: almond toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, egg and extract.
Mix well.
Stir in toffee pieces and almonds. Spread evenly over prepared crust.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: egg salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: mamma's pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: a.b.c. chili
directions: In heavy iron pot saute onion and garlic in olive oil until golden.
Add beef and brown thoroughly.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 hours. Remove bay leaf.

title: pauline's 2 hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and shortening, then add flour a small amount at a time, mixing well with spoon. When dough is too stiff to stir, pour out onto well floured board. Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in well-greased bowl and sit in warm place (not hot) to rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Make out with hands into rolls, placing in well-greased baking pan.
Let rise until double again (about 1 hour).
Bake in 450° oven.

title: christmas stollen
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cake mix and flour and knead dough.
Let rise until double.
Roll to 1/4 inch thickness and spread with brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Roll as for jelly roll and cut 1/2-inch slices.

title: my face sandwich
directions: Cut out circle shapes in bread with doughnut cutter.
Top 1 slice bread with peanut butter.
Add honey, yeast and raisins.
Top with other circle of bread.
Have fun eating!
Don't throw out scraps of bread, but have fun making designs in your plate and eating as well.

title: sandy's muffins
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar and add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and
salt.
Add sifted mixture alternately with milk.
Fold in floured blueberries or other fruit and 1 teaspoon of vanilla. Bake in muffin tins at 400° for 25 minutes.
Yields 14 large muffins or 2 dozen small muffins.

title: apple tarts
directions: Cut apple into slices.
Insert into big end of crescent roll. Roll and place (long side down) in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Let ice cream soften.
Meanwhile, crush Oreos in blender real fine.
Fold in Cool Whip to softened ice cream; add crushed Oreos. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and refreeze.
Best to freeze at least 24 hours before eating.
Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: almond bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs and sugar until lemon colored. Add butter, flour and extract.
Mix well.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30-35 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners Sugar.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: salsa
directions: Chop all vegetables into chunks.
In a heavy pan, simmer tomatoes, onion, green pepper, and jalapenos for 3 hours with the lid off.
Stir constantly; after about 2 to 2 1/2 hours, add salt and sugar.
Pour sauce in jars and boil for 10 minutes.

title: jo's hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in casserole.
Pour 1/2 of margarine on potatoes.
Layer cream of chicken soup, onions, cheese slices and sour cream.
Top with corn flakes.
Pour on rest of margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: queen of puddings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the yolks of eggs light and add sugar and the soft butter.
Mix well.
Add milk, then add bread crumbs.
Stir.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake like a custard by putting the dish in a pan of water.
Place in oven. When baked, spread over with strawberries, cover with egg whites beaten stiff with 1/2 cup sugar.
Brown in oven.
Sift sugar over meringue.
Eat with sugar and cream when hot or cold.

title: peach yogurt muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat 12-cup muffin pan with vegetable spray.
Combine egg whites, yogurt, honey, oil and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in peaches.
Fold in dry ingredients with spatula until combined; do not overmix.
Spoon into muffin pans.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Turn out on rack.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: pizza pockets
directions: Heat snakmaster.
Butter one side of bread on both pieces. Flip so butter is touching.
Spread pizza sauce on bread.
Put your peperonie on and cheese.
Put in snack master for 2 minutes. You have Pizza Pockets.

title: spanish flan
directions: In a small saucepan combine the sugar and water, put over a low heat amd stir until the sugar dissolves.
Increase heat to medium high and bring to a boil without stirring.
Continue to boil until it turns a caramel color, about 8-10 minutes.
Quickly pour over the bottom and sides of 8 custard cups or a 1 1/2 qt. glass casserole dish.
Combine the eggs, evaporated milk, condensed milk and vanilla, mix together for 1 minute at medium speed until well blended.
Pour over caramel mixture.
Place the custard cups/casserole dish into a large baking pan with about 1 inch of hot water in the bottom.
Bake at 325°f. 160°c. gas mark 3 for 35-40 minutes or until set.
Refrigerate overnight.
To serve first loosen the sides with a sharp knife, invert onto plates and give a good shake, they will fall out!

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and sage.
Sear slowly.
Turn to brown.
Place in large baking dish.
Slice apples 1/3-inch rings. Arrange on chops and sprinkle with broth sugar.
Add flour to fat in skillet and cook until brown.
Add water and stir until it boils.
Add vinegar, salt and raisins.
Pour sauce over chops. Cover and bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serves 6.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir only until moistened.
Pour in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: grande dip
directions: Mix together really well.
Put into small ovenproof dish (I use soup crock).
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake about 15 minutes, the last 2 to 3 minutes sprinkle sliced Spanish olives over top.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: grilling herb mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in tightly sealed jar.

title: potato casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix ingredients together and spread in pan.
Sprinkle bits and cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cashew nut stuffing
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter in skillet until tender.
Add mixture to bread cubes and cashews.
Mix in seasonings, water, wine and egg.
Stuff bird immediately and roast.
Makes 8 cups, enough to stuff a 12 pound turkey.

title: tortilla crunch chicken fingers
directions: In a medium bowl, combine fiesta herb with red pepper soup mix and tortilla chips.
In a large plastic bag or bowl, combine chicken and egg (beaten with water), coating well.
Dip chicken in tortilla mixture, coating well.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix vegetables, chicken and chicken soup together.
Put in pie shell.
Bake until brown in 350° oven.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and Crisco until light and fluffy (about 10 minutes) using electric mixer. Add eggs and vanilla and beat well. Sift flour, baking soda and salt together and add to creamed mixture a little at a time. Add the oats and pecans. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet covered with foil, shiny side down. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Let cool on the foil. Cookies and/or dough may be frozen.

title: creamy french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. Cut 6 cherries in half and reserve. Also chop rest of fruit up and add to the cream cheese mixture along with the nuts. Fold in Cool Whip. Put in foil cupcake holders in muffin tins and garnish top of each with an orange slice and 1/2 of cherry. Freeze until solid and put in freezer bags. Ready to eat whenever you want; better if taken out about 15 to 30 minutes before eating. Yummy!!

title: crush-stuff-cheese ball
directions: Mix together softened cheeses.
Add seasonings and about 1/2 cup of crushed stuffing mix.
Mix well.
Form into a ball or several smaller balls as per choice.
Roll in additional stuffing mix.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate until serving time.

title: spaghetti and sauce
directions: Brown meatballs or ground beef and drain well.
If you are using meatballs remove them from the skillet, otherwise add remaining ingredients except spaghetti and cheese.
Bring mixture to a boil, add meatballs if using them, cover and simmer for
20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
While sauce is simmering cook spaghetti
according to
package directions.
Serve over spaghetti and top with parmesan cheese.

title: dit plash seafood gumbo(learned from charlie)
directions: Saute the bell	peppers, onions and celery in oil.
Add tomato sauce, tomato, water, salt, pepper, cayenne pepper, bay leaves, and Worcestershire	sauce.	Make about 2 cups of flour in oil for roux
and
add to above.
Let boil 10 minutes.
Add crabmeat and shrimp.
Let
boil	15 minutes.
Add okra and let boil about 20 minutes, stirring often.
Serve over rice.

title: apricot bars
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; stir in oats and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 of crumbs in an 11 x 7-inch pan. Spread with preserves; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: spinach or broccoli balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: noodles
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl.
Beat eggs and add to flour mixture with water and oil.
Mix with fork and then knead for 10 minutes. Cover with a towel for 10 minutes.
Dough should not be sticky. Flour counter and roll as for jelly roll and cut to desired width. Separate and unroll and let dry on counter until completely dry. Lift with fingers.
May be frozen uncooked.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry bacon; chop and set aside.
Mix onion, garlic, oregano and parsley together and set aside.
In 5 tablespoons olive oil, brown the ground round.
To the ground round, add the bacon, onion mixture and the remaining ingredients.
Add water as required while cooking.
Simmer, covered, 2 or 3 hours.

title: strawberry crunch
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients and spread in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350°, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes. Sprinkle 2/3 of the crumbs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk in 6 c. casserole.
Mix in tuna, noodles, beans/peas and onion.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in hot oven 400° for 25 minutes.
May use white sauce in place of soup. Serves 4.

title: corn bread and sausage pie
directions: Fry sausage, drain. Break into small pieces. Follow directions on corn bread mix. Add sausage. Pour in greased 9 inch round cake pan. Bake at 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry shakes
directions: In blender, place all ingredients, except ice.
Cover and blend at medium speed until smooth.
Increase speed to high; add ice cubes, one at a time, until all are finely crushed.

title: wassail
directions: Boil water and tea bags gently for 10 minutes.
Mix frozen orange juice and lemonade as directed on can.
Remove tea bags from water and add diluted orange juice and lemonade, sugar and stick cinnamon.
Boil for 10 minutes longer.
Serve piping hot.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over quick oats.
Let cool while preparing the rest of the cake.
In another bowl, mix brown sugar, white sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together and stir in oatmeal mix.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Heat milk until hot.
Add all combined ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Then add 1 tablespoon vanilla.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Mix ingredients in order as given.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes in a well-greased 13 x 9 x 1-inch baking pan or dish.

title: hawaiian chili
directions: Boil pork roast until well done.
Cool and cube.
Save broth. Chop and saute peppers, celery and onions until tender.
Combine pork, peppers, celery, onions, tomatoes and beans into a large stew pot and simmer for several hours; the longer, the better.
If more liquid is needed, use broth that was saved.
Season to taste with chili powder, Tabasco sauce and cumin seed.
Serve with crackers (sourdough preferred).

title: chicken and vegetable soup
directions: Place the chicken and cold water in a pot.
Bring to a rolling boil and remove any froth that gathers on top.
Add all vegetables, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to simmer.
Cover and cook for 2 to 3 hours or until the chicken is tender and can be pulled apart.
Remove the chicken from the soup.
Remove all meat from bones and return the meat to the soup.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish and bake 35 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
This can also be mixed and refrigerated overnight before baking.

title: frosted banana peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add bananas and vanilla; beat.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to banana mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: evelyn moore's pear pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add softened cream cheese and mayonnaise to hot mixture and cool.
Drain pears and mash.
Add mashed pears and crushed pineapple (not drained) to cool jello.
When this begins to congeal, fold in a small carton of Cool Whip.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Put popped corn in large bowl and set aside.
Combine sugars, corn syrup, water, vinegar, and salt in a 2 qt. saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium-high heat, stirring frequently.
Stirring constantly after it comes to a boil, continue to cook until it reaches 260 degrees on a candy thermometer.
Reduce heat and stir in butter.
Pour syrup in thin streams over corn in bowl.
Stir corn to coat with syrup.
Cool slightly, butter hands, shape into balls, and place on waxed paper.
Yields 12 balls.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas, and nuts.
Put half of mixture in an 8 x 12-inch pan. Chill to set.
Pour sour cream over mixture in pan.
Then spoon carefully the remainder of strawberry mixture over sour cream. Refrigerate until firm.

title: cheese balls
directions: Leave cheeses at room temperature for about 2 hours.
Cream all cheeses together with garlic salt, red pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add 1/2 cup of nuts and 1/2 cup parsley. Shape into ball or log.
Roll into 1/2 cup of nuts and 1/2 cup parsley.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine squash, margarine, onion, crushed crackers, milk, mixed with beaten egg, salt, pepper and cheese.
Pour into buttered 1-quart Pyrex dish.
During the last 15 minutes, add Pepperidge Farm stuffing to cover top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pretzel candy
directions: Melt pieces and peanut butter over low heat; remove from stove and add pretzels and nuts.
Spread on greased (buttered) cookie sheet.
Break into pieces.

title: walnut glory cake
directions: Sift flour with cinnamon and salt.
Beat egg whites in large mixing bowl until soft mound forms.
Gradually add 3/4 cup of the sugar.
Continue beating until very stiff and straight peak forms (do not underbeat).
Combine egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla in small mixing bowl.
Beat until thick and lemon-colored.
Stir in dry ingredients and beat good.
Fold batter gently, but thoroughly, into egg whites using a whisk or spatula, fold in walnuts.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool completely upside down before removing from pan.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine using low heat, stir occasionally and saute until onions are transparent.
Add beef broth, 1 can cold water and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Divide into 4 cups.
Remember to use cup or bowl that can be broiled in oven. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Top with croutons and 1 slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Broil for 5 minutes or until light brown and bubbly.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies
in
blender.
Combine
and
blend
until thick pudding,
milk
and vanilla.
Combine margarine, whipped topping, cream cheese
and powdered sugar.
Using a flower pot or sand pail,
alternate
layers
of "dirt" (Oreo cookies) and pudding and whipped topping, ending with "dirt".
Refrigerate. May be decorated with gummy worms, flowers, etc.
Use a shovel to serve.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Peel pears and halve or quarter them; place in large pot or pan.
Sprinkle heavily with sugar.
Cover in water and let set overnight.
Cook on low heat about 6 hours or if smaller amount until pears get done and syrup is thick.
Place in jars and seal. Ready to eat.

title: judy's steak soup
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
In soup pot, place water and all veggies.
Add meat, seasonings and wine.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: overnight buns
directions: Boil the water and sugar for five minutes, cool and add the rest of ingredients.
Set at
3:00 P.M. and let rise until 5:00 P.M.
Knead down and let rise at least 2 times.
Form into buns and place in pans at 9:30 P.M. or later.
Keep in a cool place overnight.
Bake in the morning in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: angel food cake with pineapple icing
directions: Mix pineapple, pudding mix and Cool Whip together and ice prepared angel food cake.
Quick, easy and good.

title: oven fried cheesy italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Heat butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan until melted.
Mix remaining dry ingredients.
Coat chicken. Place skin side down on pan.
Bake 35 minutes; turn chicken and bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar over medium heat.
Cool 2 minutes. Add
1 egg
at
a time; mix thoroughly.
Add flour; mix well. Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: italian shrimp
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add shrimp, mushrooms and garlic. Cover and cook on medium heat for about 10 minutes or until shrimp are pink.
Uncover; stir in sherry and parsley.
Cover and simmer for about five minutes.
Remove from heat and sprinkle cheese generously.
Serve with crunchy Italian bread, salad and chilled white wine.
Serves 4.

title: ultimate burgers
directions: Carefully mix the meats, steak sauce, egg yolks, salt and pepper with the tines of a fork, but do not mash it. Lightly form each burger and lightly press into a patty shape. Make an indention and put a thin slice of butter inside each burger, making sure the butter is entirely encased in the meat. Grill or broil as you would any other burger.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in large mixing bowl and mix well. Pour other ingredients over flour mixture and stir.
Do not beat. Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender in salt water; drain.
Cook ground beef and onion until meat changes color.
Drain off fat.
Mix sugar and tomatoes.
Stir meat, tomatoes, soup, cheese and black pepper into the macaroni.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Add more salt, if needed.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown and season hamburger.
Drain fat and stir in 1/2 cup cheese.
Set aside.
In saucepan heat tomato soup, mushroom soup and enchilada sauce.
Dip corn shell in sauce; fill with meat. Roll and place in baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over rolled enchiladas and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pear salad with raspberry cream
directions: Whisk together first 4 ingredients.
Set dressing aside. Peel pears, if desired; quarter and core pears.
Brush with lemon juice.
Arrange Bibb and romaine lettuces on 4 plates.
Arrange pear quarters over lettuce.
Drizzle with dressing; sprinkle salad with Parmesan cheese, crumbled bacon and raspberries.

title: hot water gingerbread
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed, dissolving soda in boiling water.
Bake in a shallow pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Crumble leftover biscuits in bottom of pan.
Pour canned peaches with juice over top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, nutmeg and brown sugar.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: acini de pepe salad
directions: Drain and save juice from cans of fruit.
Store fruit in refrigerator overnight.

title: peach salad
directions: Put in 9x13 buttered pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll quartered biscuits in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in greased Bundt pan.
Bring brown sugar, butter and cinnamon to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until golden brown.
Pull apart and eat with your hands.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients together in a bowl.
Form meat into patties.
Place patties in the refrigerator for about 30 minutes before cooking.
Grill outside on outdoor grill or on an inside grill.
Baste patties with barbecue sauce while cooking. Cook about 5 to 7 minutes on each side.
Place a slice of fat-free cheese on each patty for the last minute of cooking time.
Serve on low-fat buns with lettuce, tomato and any other garnish you desire. If using mayonnaise, be sure to use the Kraft fat-free variety. Makes 8 burgers.

title: fudgy coconut pie
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs, butter, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in pecans and coconut. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Put in refrigerator for 3 hours.
You can use whipped cream on top.
Make sure it's whipped.

title: green beans with zucchini and bacon
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, prepare green beans as label directs but cook only half as long as directed; drain.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble. Set aside.
Pour fat from skillet; wipe skillet clean with paper towels.
To skillet, add butter or margarine and onion; cook until onion is tender, about 3 minutes.
Increase heat to medium-high. Add zucchini and cook, stirring quickly and frequently, until just tender-crisp, about 4 minutes.
Stir in crumbled bacon, green beans, salt and pepper and cook about 1 minute longer or until beans are hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 475° until golden brown.

title: stew
directions: Roll meat in seasoned flour.
Brown meat in oil.
While browning meat start boiling veggies.
Add meat to mixture.
Boil until tender.
Take 1/4 cup seasoned flour and 2 packages gravy mix and add to water to make smooth paste.
Add to mixture to thicken.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Spoon blobs of dough onto ungreased sheets.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes until light brown.
Store in refrigerator to keep from getting stale.

title: salmon and rice bake
directions: Butter a 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish with 2 tablespoons butter or oleo.
Clean salmon and break apart in a bowl.
Stir in egg and cooked rice; add milk.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan and cover with coarsely crushed soda crackers (about 3/4 cup).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Knead and roll out. Cut out rolls and let rise 3 hours.
Bake.

title: pear pie
directions: In a 8 x 13 inch rectangular baking dish, melt butter in a 350 degree oven.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour and spices together. Add flour mixture evenly on top of melted butter, then add milk and pears with juice.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender and skin.
Let potatoes cool completely, then grate them, using the largest hole on the grater. Add sour cream, cheese, green onion, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly and press into a 2-quart greased baking dish.
Add some grated cheese to the top and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 cup melted butter and all other ingredients, except corn flakes.
Pour into greased casserole.
Mix corn flakes and other 1/2 cup butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, crumbled bacon and grated cheese.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over salad mixture.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: do it yourself quiche
directions: Beat together eggs, half and half, salt and pepper.
Toss together meat, cheese and flour.
Add to egg mixture.
Pour into crust.
Bake pie on cookie sheet in 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Drain cooked carrots.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and ginger.
Add orange juice.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more. Stir in margarine.
Pour over hot carrots, stirring lightly to coat.

title: zesty apple walnut salad
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°. In small bowl, combine butter and Worcestershire sauce; add walnuts, stirring to coat. Let stand for a few minutes so walnuts can absorb the liquid. Spread walnuts on a baking sheet and place in oven for 15 minutes.

title: lemon bars #2
directions: Work flour, shortening, powdered sugar and salt as you would pie crust and press into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen daiquiri
directions: Mix and freeze in glass jar or plastic jar.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Bring pepper, sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add coloring.
Add pectin and boil 1 more minute. Remove from heat.
Let set 5 minutes.
Strain and pour into hot jars.
Seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: cecily brownstone chicken
directions: Preheat Broiler.
Cut up chicken, wash and dry. (remove skin if you wish).
Melt butter and add all other ingredients. Pour over chicken in baking pan. Broil until brown, turn, baste and brown again. Takes about 45 min. to cook through.

title: rolls
directions: Mix together and pour in a muffin pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: one bar lye soap
directions: Mix the water and lye; let cool.
Add the ammonia and Borax or Borateem.
Pour into a 1-cup strainer.
Cool grease to room temperature.
Stir until creamy and thick.
Pour into small container to set (a matchbox or a small plastic margarine container).
Vinegar will neutralize lye.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spread in sprayed or greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: austrian apfelspalten(apple fritters)
directions: Beat milk, flour and salt together.
Stir in the egg, sugar and rum and continue to beat.
The batter will be thick.
Peel apples; core and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip apples in the batter and fry in hot butter.
Drain.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and confectioners sugar or serve with maple syrup.

title: chicken breasts in wine sauce
directions: Lightly brown breasts (salted and peppered) in margarine. Place in baking dish, not overlapping.
Pour all other ingredients in frying pan over heat.
Mix.
When combined, pour over chicken pieces.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, covered with aluminum foil. Bake another 1/2 hour at 350°, uncovered, to brown.
Serve over wild rice.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat the eggs.	Mix in the
oil and water.
Stir in the pumpkin pie filling.
Mix
together
flour,
sugar, soda, salt and spices and stir into
the
pumpkin	mixture.
Mix well and put in pans and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Saute onions and add to ground beef.
Mix tomatoes, enchilada sauce, mushroom and chicken soup with ground beef.
Cut tortillas into pieces.
Layer meat sauce with tortilla pieces as follows:
Begin with meat sauce, tortillas, sauce, tortillas, sauce.
Top with grated cheese. Place this in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: microwaved strawberry jam
directions: Chop strawberries and place in 3-quart casserole with pectin. Stir well.
Cover.
Pace in microwave oven and heat at Full power, 8 to 10 minutes until mixture is at a rolling boil.
Add sugar to boiling mixture and stir well.
Return uncovered to microwave oven and heat at Full power, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes until mixture reaches a full rolling boil.
Let boil 1 minute longer.
Remove from oven and skim off foam with metal spoon, stirring jam for 5 minutes.
Ladle into hot sterilized glasses. Seal.
Makes 8 cups.

title: veal marsala
directions: Lightly
season
the
very thin pieces of veal with salt and pepper.
Dredge
lightly
in
flour that has been spread on plate or
sheet
of
waxed
paper,
being
careful
not to coat heavily; shake
off
excess flour.
In a large, heavy skillet, melt butter or
margarine.
Add
veal
to
the hot pan.
Saute briefly and quickly
to brown lightly, about 2 minutes on each side.
Lower heat,
spoon lemon juice over meat, add the wine, cover and cook 2 minutes.
Transfer meat to serving dish.
Stir up any browned bits in pan.
Let liquid cook down a little over high
heat
if
you think
necessary.
Spoon
sauce over veal. Sprinkle with chopped parsley if desired.

title: cheese and pepper squares
directions: Line a 9-inch glass dish with peppers.
Cover with grated cheese.
Pour beaten eggs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut in squares.

title: oatmeal chocolate raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheets with shortening. Combine shortening, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended. Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in chocolate-covered raisins.

title: yuma dump cake
directions: Dump together; mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in long Pyrex dish and add mixed vegetables. Mix soup and broth and pour over above.
Mix flour, milk and melted butter and pour over top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: christmas jello salad
directions: Dissolve cherry jello in 1 cup boiling water and 1 cup pineapple juice; let set.
In second pan dissolve 1 or 2 packages lime jello.
Dice 1/2 pound marshmallows in hot jello.
Allow to cool.
Add drained crushed pineapple, mayo, cream cheese, broken pecans and Cool Whip.
Combine with the lime and marshmallow mixture when room temperature.
When red jello is firm, pour the lime and fruit on top.
Return to refrigerator.
Let set 24 hours. Serve.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Crust:
Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Let cool.

title: banana ice cream sandwiches
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine pudding and milk.
Mix on low speed until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Chill until set, about 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread 1/3 cup of pudding mixture on 8 graham crackers.
